subject: Our recommendation: Lead Data Engineer
body:
Hello Divyaprakash,

We recommend this job for you. Take a look and see if you want to apply.



Lead Data Engineer

Harvey Nash
City of London, London

Permanent

Up to £110000.00 per annum

1 day ago





Apply Now
https://click.cwjobs.co.uk/f/a/Uzp9Iw_5VobQX_eTZpXxUQ~~/AAAmIgA~/RgRpdJX6P4RHAWh0dHBzOi8vd3d3LmN3am9icy5jby51ay9Kb2JTZWFyY2gvRW1haWxMaW5rLmFzcHg_-xCSZxEQaD1SGXJkaXZ5YXByYWthc2g3OEBnbWFpbC5jb21YBAAAAAs~


Our client is a global leader in Commodities Trading, with over $50 billion in revenue annually. They're looking for a Lead Data Engineer to join their global trade surveillance team and help to manage the impacts from new business initiatives.
Title: Lead Data Engineer
Salary: £100,000-£110,000
Hybrid: 2-3 x a week in Central London office
They're looking for a Lead Data Engineer to join this newly established Trade Surveillance team, to help them grow this important business area. You will managing a team consisting of local, offshore, and 3rd party resources.
Key Requirements:
Strong Python and Pyspark experience
Extensive experience with both Data Warehouse and Data Lakehousing is a must, in particular DataBricks, SQL, Azure Data Factory (ADF)
Experience working within a Azure environment is essential
Development of ETL Pipelines, working with Big Data technologies, and data architectures is required
Automation experience e.g., PyTest
Experience with containerized environments

Nice to Have:
Capital Markets/Commodities Trading experience

If you have the above experience and would like to be considered for this position, please click apply now.
Please Note: Unfortunately, sponsorship is not an option for this role.

Read the full job description here
https://click.cwjobs.co.uk/f/a/1ZNha6qzNwMfsf5rGirNBw~~/AAAmIgA~/RgRpdJX6P4RCAWh0dHBzOi8vd3d3LmN3am9icy5jby51ay9Kb2JTZWFyY2gvRW1haWxMaW5rLmFzcHg_

subject: My January sale is now on!
body:
New Promotional Announcement

Hi Divyaprakash, an announcement has been made from Phillip, instructor of PL-300 certification prep: Microsoft Power BI Data Analyst.

Hello everyone, and thank you for joining me in the above course.

What do you want to learn in the first three months of the year?

  • Is it SQL Server: T-SQL, SSAS, SSIS, or maybe SSRS? What about Azure Database Administration?

  • What about Reporting Software? Tableau, Power BI, or Crystal Reports?

  • Do you want to learn a new skill at the Fundamental level, or higher? Microsoft Azure, Security, Programming or Databases?

  • How about Power Platform: Power Apps, Power Automate, Power BI and more?

  • Is it Microsoft Office: Word, Excel, PowerPoint or Access?

  • Or do you want a shorter course, to learn one particular skill?

It's perfectly achievable to learn one of these (or more than one) in the next few months. Why not go for it?

My January sale is now on. Udemy have been having mini-sales, but the prices they have been charging are higher than I can offer you in this sale. Unfortunately, Udemy has changed the voucher system, so I can no longer give you a specific price.

However, I can say that, if you click on any of the links in the below email, or use the voucher code JANUARY2025, you will get “the lowest price Udemy would offer any student for this course”. In other words, you will not get a better price for my courses than by using the links in this email.

The only way you will find out how little all my courses cost is by clicking on the below links. But hurry - this offer ends on Monday.

Sounds interesting? Here’s some details about each course:

----

T-SQL: SQL Server Essentials in an hour: The SELECT statement

https://www.udemy.com/sql-server-essentials-in-an-hour-the-select-statement/?couponCode=JANUARY2025

Only got an hour to spare? No problem - get to grips with the SELECT statement - SELECT, FROM, WHERE, GROUP BY, HAVING and ORDER BY. We'll then look at saving your code using both views and procedures.

---

T-SQL: Sessions 1-7 in one course: Querying Microsoft SQL Server (SQL code)

https://www.udemy.com/70-461-session-2-querying-microsoft-sql-server-2012/?couponCode=JANUARY2025

In the first 7 hours of this course, you can go from no knowledge in SQL to writing SELECT statements using all 6 of the main clauses, including JOINing multiple tables together.

We'll now use that knowledge in the remaining 22 hours of this course to create views, which enable us to store these SELECT queries for future use, and triggers. We'll have a look at constraints, MERGEing, creating procedures, aggregating queries, creating sub-queries, using XML and JSON, and much, much more.

----

T-SQL: Database Fundamentals

https://www.udemy.com/course/98-364-database-fundamentals-microsoft-sql-server/?couponCode=JANUARY2025

Want to learn T-SQL, but want something a bit shorter? In this 8½ hour course, you’ll learn all of the SELECT statement’s main clauses, as well as how to create constraints, views, procedures, functions, triggers and more.

----

SQL code: SQL for Microsoft Access

https://www.udemy.com/sql-for-microsoft-access-2007-to-2016/?couponCode=JANUARY2025

Do you use Microsoft Access instead of SQL Server? Do you want to learn how to write more advanced queries in Access? And do you want your queries to be portable into both SQL Server and Access?

In this course learn how to:

  • Write SQL code, using the six SELECT clauses.

  • Use functions and formulas in your SELECT statements.

  • Create JOINs between tables and queries, including more complex joins which cannot be created using the graphical interface.

  • Write action queries and cross-queries.

----

DBA: SQL Server Database Administration (DBA)

https://www.udemy.com/70-462-sql-server-database-administration-dba/?couponCode=JANUARY2025

In this course we'll start by downloading a demonstration database, learning how to backup and restore this database, and what recovery models are appropriate for your databases, to enable you to offer Point in Time recovery.

We'll manage logins and server roles, so you can control who gets access to what data, implement and maintain indexes, improving the speed of your queries, and import and export data. We'll look at managing SQL Server Agent, so you can automate routine tasks and be alerted to problems, we'll manage and configure databases, and look at compression, both of which aid with administrating big databases. And much more.

The course will take around 10 hours to complete, but completing this will enable you to versed in Database Administration tasks, giving you hands-on experience.

----

Azure DBA: DP-300 Administering Relational Databases

https://www.udemy.com/course/dp-300-administering-relational-databases-azure-dba/?couponCode=JANUARY2025

In this course we’ll be looking at how to administrate Azure SQL Database, Azure SQL Managed Instance, and SQL Server on Azure Virtual Machines.

In this course, learn how to:

  • Plan and implement data platform resources,

  • Implement a secure environment,

  • Monitor and optimize operational resources,

  • Optimize query performance,

  • Perform automation of tasks,

  • Plan and implement a High Availability and Disaster Recovery (HADR) environment, and

  • Perform administration by using T-SQL.

By the end of this course, you should be confident with administering relational databases on Azure – and you could even enter the DP-300 Microsoft exam and (if you pass) get an official Microsoft certification. Wouldn’t that look good on your CV or resume?

----

SSAS MDX: SQL Server SSAS (Multidimensional MDX) - an Introduction

https://www.udemy.com/sql-server-ssas-multidimensional-mdx-an-introduction/?couponCode=JANUARY2025

This course is designed for the complete beginner in Multidimensional cubes, or someone who wants to refresh their memory. We’ll create a cube to start with from an ordinary database, and then I’ll ask you to create one from a special database known as a Data Warehouse. We’ll export our cube into SQL Server Management Studio and SSRS. The second part of the course is all about querying this database using the MDX language.

----

SSAS Tabular: Microsoft SSAS (Tabular DAX model) - NEW COURSE

https://www.udemy.com/microsoft-powerpivot-and-ssas-tabular-dax-model/?couponCode=JANUARY2025

In this course, you'll create your first tabular analysis in just a few minutes. After this introduction, we'll go into some detail into SQL Server’s SSAS - the initial data, and the various options that are available to you. We will go into advanced options that most people don't even know about, but which are very useful.

Then we'll develop DAX formulas, to further extend the model. A lot of DAX formulas are based on Excel, but there are several additional formulas as well.

By the end, you will be an Expert user of the Tabular version of SSAS, able to create reliable analyses in Excel and elsewhere which are able to be drilled-down quickly, and you'll be able to help others with their data analysis.

----

SSRS: Microsoft SQL Server Reporting Services (SSRS)

https://www.udemy.com/microsoft-sql-server-reporting-services-ssrs/?couponCode=JANUARY2025

In this course, we'll create various reports, developing our skills bit by bit. As part of designing a report, we will:

  • Select report components (matrix, table, chart and other data visualisation component),

  • Identify the data source and parameters,

  • Design a grouping structure, and

  • Create drilldown reports and drillthrough reports.

We'll look closely at implementing a report layout and interactivity in a report. By the end of this course, you should be confident in creating your own reports in SSRS.

----

SSIS: SQL Server Integration Services (SSIS) - An Introduction

https://www.udemy.com/sql-server-ssis-an-introduction/?couponCode=JANUARY2025

What is SSIS? It’s a way to automate in the importing and exporting and data – or ETL: extract, transform and load. It’s a very visual part of SSIS, using tasks, components and flowcharts, so it’s easy to learn the basics of it.

We’ll start by extracting some data, and then loading it into another table. I’ll take nice as slow as we start to introduce transformations, such as aggregation, conditional split, merging and auditing. There’ll be plenty of practice activities too, so you can get to practice your new-found skills.

----

REPORTING COURSES


Power BI: PL-300 Microsoft Power BI Data Analyst

https://www.udemy.com/course/70-778-analyzing-and-visualizing-data-with-power-bi/?couponCode=JANUARY2025

Power BI is one of the most requested reporting tools that are requested in the job market, and the ability to being able to use it now could be very useful for your current work, and your next job hunt.

This course comes in four parts:

  • Part 1 - Creating Visualizations (also known as Visualize the Data, and Analyze the Data)

  • Part 2 - Get and Transform Data (also known as Prepare the Data), using the DAX language

  • Part 3 - Refining the model (also known as Model the Data), using the M language

  • Part 4 - Power BI Service

At the end of the course, you will be proficient in Power BI. And with a bit of practice, you could also go for the official Microsoft PL-300 exam - wouldn’t that certificate look good on your CV or resume? And if you are an American college student, you might even get college credit for passing that exam.


Power BI and Fabric: DP-600 Fabric Analytics Engineer Associate

https://www.udemy.com/course/dp-600-implementing-analytics-solutions-using-microsoft-fabric/?couponCode=JANUARY2025

Our DP-600 course develops on the skills you have learned in the PL-300 Power BI course, with advanced data modelling and Microsoft Fabric for data analysts.

  • Part 1 - Advanced data modelling. We'll go further into semantic models and relationships and learn new DAX formulas.

  • Part 2 - Microsoft Fabric. This can hold the data online which you can then use in the Power BI Service. We'll load data and query it using SQL.

Tableau: Data Analyst and Desktop Specialist Associate certification

https://www.udemy.com/course/tableau-2018-tableau-10-qualified-associate-certification/?couponCode=JANUARY2025

In this course, we’ll look at how to create Tableau visualisations (vizzes), dashboards and stories. We'll create maps, hierarchies, groups and sets, and all sorts of chart types. We'll enhance our charts with reference lines and bands, and extend our data analysis with trends and forecasting. We'll add formula calculations, quick table calculations, and LOD calculations. Finally, we investigate advanced data connections and mapping, together with some things you can do in the full Tableau Creator.

This course has been updated this month in line with the new Data Analyst certification, as well as supporting the Desktop Specialist certification. With some practice, you can then enter these certifications and, once earned, add them to your CV or resume.


Oracle SQL: 1Z0-171 Learn Oracle SQL and prepare for the Certified Associate certification

https://www.udemy.com/course/1z0-171-oracle-database-23ai-sql-associate/?couponCode=JANUARY2025

We start off this course by looking at the six principal clauses of the SELECT statement: SELECT, FROM, WHERE, GROUP BY, HAVING and ORDER BY. We’ll then expand this by creating views and sub queries, combining tables together using JOINs, self-JOINs and UNION, plus much more.

By the end of this course you could, with some practice, enter into the Oracle 1Z0-171 exam and earn an official Oracle certification.


Crystal Reports: An Introduction

https://www.udemy.com/course/crystal-reports-an-introduction/?couponCode=JANUARY2025

This course is separated into 7 levels, each getting progressively more deeper into Crystal Reports. They are:

1. Creating your first report,

2. Adding grouping, sorting and filtering, also known as Selecting.

3. Formatting,

4. Adding user interaction through parameters,

5. Graphs and charts,

6. Subreports, and

7. Formulas.

By the end, you will be able to develop your own reports, and start to explore other people's.

----

SHORTER AZURE AND GANTT CHART COURSES (3 hours or less)

Develop generative AI solutions with Azure OpenAI Service.

https://www.udemy.com/course/microsoft-applied-skills-develop-generative-ai-solutions-azure-openai/?couponCode=JANUARY2025

Generate natural language responses, apply prompt engineering techniques and generate and improve code using an Azure OpenAI resource, and the portal, C# or Python. You’ll also use OpenAI on your own data, and generate images with DALL-E.


Build an Azure AI Vision solution

https://www.udemy.com/course/microsoft-applied-skills-build-an-azure-ai-vision-solution/?couponCode=JANUARY2025

This allows you to use Artificial Intelligence to analyse images, create captions, retrieve text, tag images, and much more.


Create an intelligent document processing solution with Azure AI Document Intelligence.

https://www.udemy.com/course/microsoft-applied-skills-azure-ai-document-intelligence/?couponCode=JANUARY2025

Read text from images (OCR - Optical Character Recognition), using general-purpose models, and other models such as those designed especially to read invoices.


Build a natural language processing solution with Azure AI Language.

https://www.udemy.com/course/microsoft-applied-skills-azure-ai-language/?couponCode=JANUARY2025

Analyse text, identifying the language, extracting key phrases, recognise entities (such as dates, addresses, recipients and more) and sentiment, and more.


Azure Files and Azure Blob Storage.

https://www.udemy.com/course/microsoft-applied-skills-azure-files-and-azure-blob-storage/?couponCode=JANUARY2025

Store your images and files in the cloud using Azure Storage, and then secure them so that only permitted people can access them.


Project Management: Gantt Charts in an hour.

https://www.udemy.com/course/project-management-gantt-charts-in-an-hour/?couponCode=JANUARY2025

You'll learn how to plan and build Gantt charts, from defining project scope to breaking down tasks and milestones, with creating relationships between tasks and resource management.

---
FUNDAMENTAL LEVEL…OR ABOVE

Programming

In these courses, we will look at:

  • Core programming fundamentals, such as decision structures, repetition and error handling,

  • Object-oriented programming fundamentals, such as classes, inheritance, polymorphism and encapsulation,

  • General software development fundamentals: application life cycle management, application specifications, and algorithms and data structures,

  • Web applications fundamentals: web page development, Microsoft ASP NET web application development, web hosting and web services,

  • Desktop application fundamentals, namely Windows apps, console-based applications and Windows Services, and

  • Databases fundamentals, including query methods and database connection methods.

To learn about programming:

  • For C#, please go to https://www.udemy.com/course/98-361-software-development-fundamentals-using-c-sharp/?couponCode=JANUARY2025

  • For VB Net, please go to https://www.udemy.com/course/98-361-software-development-fundamentals-using-vb-net-visual-basic-net/?couponCode=JANUARY2025

----

Databases

https://www.udemy.com/course/98-364-database-fundamentals-microsoft-sql-server/?couponCode=JANUARY2025

In this course, we will look at how to:

  • Create tables in a database, normalize the tables, and ALTER columns in the table.

  • know what data type to use in various situations.

  • retrieve data using SELECT, FROM, WHERE, GROUP BY, HAVING and ORDER BY.

  • JOIN two tables together, finding missing data.

  • INSERT new data, UPDATE and DELETE existing data, and export data INTO a new table.

  • Create constraints, views, procedures and triggers

  • Create backups and restore data, and investigate security

----

AZURE

Microsoft Azure - Generally (AZ-900)

https://www.udemy.com/course/az-900-microsoft-azure-fundamentals-exam-preparation/?couponCode=JANUARY2025

In the first of my Azure courses, we will look at Azure generally:

  • Cloud concepts, core Azure services, and core solutions and management tools on Azure,

  • General Security and network security features,

  • Identity, governance, privacy, and compliance features, and

  • Azure cost management and Service Level Agreements.

----

Microsoft Azure - Data (DP-900)

https://www.udemy.com/course/dp-900-microsoft-azure-data-fundamentals-course/?couponCode=JANUARY2025

In the second of my Azure courses, you can concentrate on data and databases in Azure, with a little bit of Power BI as well:

  • Understand types of core data workloads and data analytics core concepts,

  • Understand how to work with relational data on Azure, including Azure SQL Database and Managed Instance,

  • Understand how to work with non-relational data on Azure, including Cosmos DB APIs, Table, Blob and File storage,

  • Describe analytics workloads, including data warehouses, data ingestion and processing on Azure, and

  • Describe data visualization in Microsoft Power BI, including reports and dashboards.

----

Microsoft Azure and Microsoft 365 - Microsoft Security, Compliance and Identity Fundamentals (SC-900)

https://www.udemy.com/course/sc-900-microsoft-security-complianceidentity-fundamentals/?couponCode=JANUARY2025

In the third of my Azure courses, which also includes Microsoft 365, we will look at:

  • Describe the concepts of security, compliance, and identity,

  • Describe the capabilities of Microsoft identity and access management solutions,

  • Describe the capabilities of Microsoft security solutions, and

  • Describe the capabilities of Microsoft compliance solutions.

----

Power Platform - Power BI, Power Apps, Power Automate and more (PL-900, PL-100, PL-200 and PL-400)

This course is an introduction to the Power Platform:

  • Describe the business value of Microsoft's Power Platform,

  • Identify the Core Components of Power Platform, including Dataverse (CDS), Connectors and AI Builder, and

  • Demonstrate the capabilities of Power BI, Power Apps, Power Automate and Power Virtual Agents.

PL-900: To learn about the Power Platform at the Foundation level, which looks at the theory of the Power Platform, please go to https://www.udemy.com/course/pl-900-microsoft-power-platform-fundamentals-r/?couponCode=JANUARY2025

PL-200 Part 1: To learn about the Power Platform at a more advanced and practical level, please go to https://www.udemy.com/course/pl-100-microsoft-power-platform-app-maker-ms/?couponCode=JANUARY2025

PL-200 Part 2: To build on what you have learnt in the Part 1 course, have a look at my Part 2 course by going to https://www.udemy.com/course/pl-200-microsoft-power-platform-functional-consultant-course/?couponCode=JANUARY2025

PL-400: To extend the Power Platform user experience and platform using JavaScript/TypeScript and C#, have a look at my PL-400 course by going to https://www.udemy.com/course/pl-400-microsoft-power-platform-developer-course/?couponCode=JANUARY2025

----

Create processes using Power Automate

https://www.udemy.com/course/microsoft-applied-skills-processes-using-power-automate/?couponCode=JANUARY2025

Create automated processes, for when new data arrives, on a timetable, or when you need it. Create actions based on that data, approvals for requests for leave, and implement conditional logic.

----

Create canvas apps with Power Apps

https://www.udemy.com/course/microsoft-applied-skills-create-canvas-apps-with-power-apps/?couponCode=JANUARY2025

Create a 3-screen app in the cloud, upload your data, and use the app to add new and modify existing data.

----

Create and manage model-driven apps with Power Apps and Dataverse

https://www.udemy.com/course/microsoft-applied-skills-create-model-driven-power-apps-and-dataverse/?couponCode=JANUARY2025

Create a model-driven app, using Dataverse tables, forms and views in a Dataverse solution.

----

Dynamics 365 CRM (MB-910)

https://www.udemy.com/course/mb-910-microsoft-dynamics-365-fundamentals-crm-v/?couponCode=JANUARY2025

In this Fundamentals course, we’ll look at Dynamics 365 Marketing, Sales, Customer Service and Field Service. We’ll get free trials of the various Dynamics 365 apps, so you can try it on your computer.

----

MICROSOFT OFFICE

Microsoft Office for PC

Want to be certified in Microsoft Office? In this course, you'll learn all of the requirements of the MO-100, MO-200 and MO-300 exams. That's Word, Excel and PowerPoint all in the one course – all of the requirements of the Microsoft Office Specialist: Associate certification.

https://www.udemy.com/course/microsoft-office-specialist-associate-word-mo-100-excel-mo-200-mo-300/?couponCode=JANUARY2025

----

My Excel 1 and 2 courses each are about 11 hours long, and take you from absolute beginner to an Expert. You could (and others have) take a Microsoft Excel Expert exam, and with other exams, you could get an official Office Expert or Office Master certification - how would that look on your resume or CV?

There are plenty of practice activities as you go, so you can be sure that you are learning.

Excel 1 PC (MO-210 exam)

https://www.udemy.com/course/mo-210-microsoft-excel-microsoft-365-apps/?couponCode=JANUARY2025

Excel 2 PC (MO-211 exam - more advanced)

https://www.udemy.com/course/mo-211-microsoft-excel-expert-microsoft-365-apps/?couponCode=JANUARY2025

---

Or maybe you want to learn more about PivotTables. There is a lot of functionality that others don't know about, but you could learn very quickly.

The PC version of this course also includes the very useful Get and Transform (Power Query) and Power Pivot – something every Excel expert should know.

Excel 3 PC (PivotTables, Power Query and Power Pivot)

https://www.udemy.com/master-pivot-tables-introduction-and-masterclass/?couponCode=JANUARY2025

---

Or how about taking your first steps in Visual Basic for Applications, and being able to automate your applications?

Excel 4 PC (VBA)

https://www.udemy.com/excel-vba-visual-basic-for-applications-an-introduction/?couponCode=JANUARY2025

---

Want more? Here's Word, PowerPoint and Access:

Microsoft Word 1

https://www.udemy.com/77-418-session-1improve-ms-word-skills-to-certificate-level/?couponCode=JANUARY2025

Microsoft Word 2

https://www.udemy.com/microsoft-word-from-intermediate-to-expert-certification/?couponCode=JANUARY2025

Microsoft Access Beginner to Specialist (Intermediate) Level

https://www.udemy.com/microsoft-access-beginner-to-specialist-intermediate-level/?couponCode=JANUARY2025

SQL for Microsoft Access

https://www.udemy.com/sql-for-microsoft-access-2007-to-2016/?couponCode=JANUARY2025

----

Microsoft Office for Mac

Got a Mac? Have a look at Microsoft Excel for Mac.

Excel Mac 1

https://www.udemy.com/microsoft-excel-go-from-beginner-to-specialist-certificate/?couponCode=JANUARY2025

Excel Mac 2 (more advanced)

https://www.udemy.com/microsoft-excel-for-mac-2-intermediate-to-expert-advanced/?couponCode=JANUARY2025

Excel Mac 3 (PivotTables)

https://www.udemy.com/excel-2016-for-mac-3-pivot-tables-intro-masterclass/?couponCode=JANUARY2025

Excel Mac 4 (VBA)

https://www.udemy.com/microsoft-excel-2016-mac-4-vba-macros-for-excel-an-intro/?couponCode=JANUARY2025

----

I hope that you found this email interesting, and that you will be able to develop your skills, and even take one or more official Microsoft certifications to add to your CV or resume.

Thank you very much for reading this - I hope to see you in these courses. Any problems, let me know. And keep learning.

Phillip

Delivered by Udemy 600 Harrison Street, 3rd Floor, San Francisco, CA 94107. You may unsubscribe if you prefer not to receive messages like these. If something isn't right, please report abuse.

subject: Your application to Barclays
body:
Subject: Divyaprakash Rathinasabapathy ‎- JR-0000022812 Data Scientist

Barclays Email Classification: Restricted - External

Dear Divyaprakash,

Unfortunately, we have decided not to progress with your application further at this time. We understand that this may be disappointing news and we appreciate the time and effort you put into your application.


We regularly check our applicant database to match candidates with roles on offer at Barclays, so if there is an opening that matches your skills, we’ll let you know. We would also encourage you to review our current opportunities at www.Barclays.com/careers.


In the meantime, we would recommend you review your candidate profile on a regular basis and keep your details up to date. Your candidate profile was created during the application process and can be accessed by clicking here

https://barclays.wd3.myworkdayjobs.com/External_Career_Site_Barclays/login?redirect=%2FExternal_Career_Site_Barclays .

As per the agreed Privacy Statement, we will keep your details on file for the specified period of time. After this, and assuming no further recruitment activity has occurred, your details will be removed from our database. If you would like to have your details removed from our database sooner than this, you can request this through your candidate profile. Requests for profile removal will be dealt with according to applicable law.


Thank you for your interest in Barclays, we sincerely hope you will consider another application in the future.



Kind regards,

Barclays Talent Acquisition Team

Commercial Analytics Manager | Health & Fitness
London | Hybrid
I am currently looking for an experienced Commercial Analytics Manager to join a rapidly scaling Health and Fitness business, that has recently undertaken some huge digital projects and is gearing up for its next wave of growth.
Reporting directly to the Senior Revenue Manager, you will play a critical role in data-driven commercial decision-making within the business. It will be your responsibility to analyse commercial performance, identify expansion opportunities, and provide data and insights that will help shape their commercial strategy.
As Commercial Analytics Manager you will need:
5+ years’ experience in an analytics role (data or commercial)
A background in Economics, Maths, Statistics or Finance
To be able to effectively analyse data and translate it into actionable insights
Recent experience in revenue forecasting and/or revenue budgeting models
Excellent stakeholder management skills
Sharp attention to detail and accuracy
Stella numerical and analytical skills

The Tech:
Strong SQL / Excel
Power BI
Modelling skills (SQL or Python or similar)

Benefits:
Complimentary gym membership
10% bonus (business & personal performance)
25 days annual leave
Learning and development pathways
Life Assurance
Pension scheme
Season ticket loans
Flexible working
Enhanced maternity pay

This is an exciting opportunity for an experienced Commercial Analytics Manager to join a growing team and play an important role in the company’s future success.
*Unfortunately, due to the high volume of applications, not all submissions will receive feedback.

subject: Our recommendation: Senior/Lead Data Scientist
body:
Hello Divyaprakash,

We recommend this job for you. Take a look and see if you want to apply.




Senior/Lead Data Scientist
Yolk Recruitment
Cardiff (CF1) Permanent £80000.00 - £95000.00 per annum 
 6 days ago

https://click.totaljobsmail.com/f/a/YdnI1S_YWmYRNJj5u_Bf4w~~/AAAmIgA~



Role - Senior/Lead Data Scientist
Location - Cardiff (Hybrid 2/3 days per week)
Salary - Dependant on experience, up to £80,000 for Senior, negotiable for Lead
Looking for a new challenge in 2025… We're seeking a skilled and enthusiastic Data Scientist to Join an innovative team at the forefront of leveraging data to drive impactful solutions. You'll play a key role in building advanced models, optimizing processes, and developing scalable data systems within a collaborative and agile environment.
*Please note that applications will be reviewed from the 2nd of Jan onwards with feedback/interviews commencing from the w/c 6th
What You'll Do
Design forecasting models and algorithms to optimize performance.
Engineer robust data pipelines to leverage diverse datasets in predictive systems.
Refine CI/CD pipelines, Infrastructure as Code (IaC), and test-driven development practices.
Collaborate across software development, data engineering, and operational teams for seamless solutions.
Provide mentorship to junior team members and foster a culture of collaboration.

What You'll Bring
3+ years of experience in data science, with hands-on expertise in Python, R, SQL, and cloud platforms (AWS, GCP, or Azure).
Proficiency in Git version control systems.
Knowledge of IaC tools (e.g., Terraform), CI/CD pipelines, and test-driven development is a plus.
A degree in a quantitative field is advantageous but not essential.

Why You Should Apply
This is more than just a job-it's an opportunity to grow, innovate, and make an impact in a fast-moving sector. In return you'll get the following:
Competitive salary + quarterly profit-sharing.
Generous holiday allowance
Private medical coverage (including dental and vision) and mental health support.
Personal training budget and paid conference attendance.
Flexibility to work from home with a collaborative in-office culture.
Annual holiday stipend (after one year).

This is your chance to join a team where your ideas, skills, and career growth are truly valued.
Ready to Apply?
Contact Lewis Allen to find out more!
Please apply with a CV and a cover letter outlining why you're perfect for the role. We also have a referral scheme so if you know of someone who would be great for the role please get in touch.
*Please note, whilst we do our best to contact all candidates, due to the high number of applications we receive we cannot guarantee this for every role. If you have not heard anything from us within 7 days of applying - then unfortunately you have been unsuccessful. Please keep an eye on our website for more opportunities.

My Client is a Leading Insurance company hiring for a Data Science Lead to join their strong team and spearhead the Data Science function! Create explanatory models to analyse the correlation between pricing and other relevant business factors
Work closely with and help mentor some of the more junior members within the Data team.
Engage with senior business stakeholders

A successful Lead Data Scientist will have the following:
Degree in STEM subject
Strong coding skills in Python and good understanding of software engineering best practices
Proven leadership/mentorship and management
Experience working end to end, deploying own models
Experience with Spark/Databricks is highly desirable
Experience deploying ML at scale via APIs
Strong experience with MLOps

subject: Our recommendation: Business Data Analyst
body:
Hello Divyaprakash,

We recommend this job for you. Take a look and see if you want to apply.




Business Data Analyst
Lloyd Recruitment Limited
Epsom (KT17) Permanent Negotiable 
 1 day ago

https://click.totaljobsmail.com/f/a/TQfR0ZpPqO002Stqs8iMRw~~/AAAmIgA~



We are supporting our long-term client in their search for an experienced Business Data Analyst. This is an excellent opportunity to join a company who are recognised as market leaders, at an exciting time of internal change and improvements.
If successful, you'll be working in a BI & Data Services team of 5 including the Team Leader. On the BI side, you'll be involved in various types of reporting including business wide dashboards, and ad hoc requests. On the Data Services side, you'll be focusing on improving and streamlining data from all sources to (re)model to make it more reportable.
Current responsibilities:
Understand the business's priorities and challenges.
Balance effort/value to help set priorities.
Gather and expand business requirements.
Work with development teams to turn requirements into solutions.
Create clear, impactful reports and dashboards using tools like Excel, Power BI, and Cognos.
Coordinate user testing and approvals.
Document processes, update the report catalogue, and maintain the business glossary.
Review outcomes to guide future projects.
Identify and help with training needs for users.

Involvement and encouragement to participate in the following areas:
Challenge the business to ensure appropriate understanding of needs
Identify opportunities for implementing data engineer and BI solutions
Support Senior Manager on pipeline reporting/analysis and backlog prioritising
Suggest improvements to processes and procedures for continuous improvement
Ad hoc projects that crop up

What we need you to have:
Solid understanding of business operations.
Experience documenting business and technical requirements.
Strong analytical and problem-solving skills.
Knowledge of IBM Cognos Suite (or similar BI tools like SQL).
Advanced Excel skills and proficiency with Microsoft Office.

The package:
Along with a very competitive basic salary, they offer an excellent benefits package, a great working culture and first-class office facilities.
This position also comes with an extended car ownership / lease scheme
Hybrid working (3 home / 2 office)
Excellent pension contribution
Personal and family targeted benefits options to allow individuals to tailor their needs to their benefits.

Refer a friend and earn up to £500!
Unfortunately, due to high numbers of applications, we are only able to respond to shortlisted applicants. If you have not heard from us within 5 days, please assume that you have not been shortlisted on this occasion.
By applying for this vacancy, you accept Lloyd Recruitment Services Privacy and GDPR Policy which can be found on our website and therefore gives us consent to contact you.
Lloyd Recruitment Services are acting as a recruitment agency in relation to this vacancy and are an equal opportunities employer.

body:
Hello Divyaprakash,

Commercial Analytics Manager | Health & Fitness
London | Hybrid
I am currently looking for an experienced Commercial Analytics Manager to join a rapidly scaling Health and Fitness business, that has recently undertaken some huge digital projects and is gearing up for its next wave of growth.
Reporting directly to the Senior Revenue Manager, you will play a critical role in data-driven commercial decision-making within the business. It will be your responsibility to analyse commercial performance, identify expansion opportunities, and provide data and insights that will help shape their commercial strategy.
As Commercial Analytics Manager you will need:
5+ years’ experience in an analytics role (data or commercial)
A background in Economics, Maths, Statistics or Finance
To be able to effectively analyse data and translate it into actionable insights
Recent experience in revenue forecasting and/or revenue budgeting models
Excellent stakeholder management skills
Sharp attention to detail and accuracy
Stella numerical and analytical skills

The Tech:
Strong SQL / Excel
Power BI
Modelling skills (SQL or Python or similar)

Benefits:
Complimentary gym membership
10% bonus (business & personal performance)
25 days annual leave
Learning and development pathways
Life Assurance
Pension scheme
Season ticket loans
Flexible working
Enhanced maternity pay

This is an exciting opportunity for an experienced Commercial Analytics Manager to join a growing team and play an important role in the company’s future success.

subject: Our recommendation: Lead Data Scientist - ML & AI projects – Kent
body:
Hello Divyaprakash,

We recommend this job for you. Take a look and see if you want to apply.




Lead Data Scientist - ML & AI projects – Kent
Datatech Analytics
Tunbridge Wells, Kent Permanent Competitive annual salary of up to £90,000 dependent on experience 
 31 days ago

https://click.totaljobsmail.com/f/a/4IWZ1cj-LLWcAMqtmyu8nw~~/AAAmIgA~-NipBUhlyZGl2eWFwcmFrYXNoNzhAZ21haWwuY29tWAQAAAAG



Lead Data Scientist - ML & AI projects
Competitive annual salary of up to £90,000 dependent on experience 
Hybrid working - West Kent office base (currently 2 days in office but expected to move to 3)
Ref J12882

Unfortunately, no sponsorship available with this client so full UK working rights required

Our client is seeking to recruit a new Lead Data Scientist to lead data science initiatives and drive innovation in the healthcare industry. You'll have the opportunity to leverage your expertise in data analysis and machine learning within our dynamic and forward-thinking team, to shape the future of healthcare. If you're passionate about making a real impact and are ready to lead a team of talented data scientists, we want to hear from you.

What you'll be doing: 
• Lead a relatively small team of data scientists in developing and implementing advanced data analytics, machine learning and traditional and generative AI solutions, to address complex challenges in healthcare. 
• Collaborate with cross-functional teams to identify business opportunities, define data science strategies, and drive the development of innovative products and services. 
• Oversee the end-to-end process of data collection, pre-processing, analysis, and model development to derive actionable insights and improve decision-making. 
• Drive the development and deployment of scalable and efficient machine learning models and algorithms to enhance healthcare services and optimize business operations. 
• Mentor and coach junior data scientists, fostering a culture of continuous learning, innovation, and excellence in data science practices.

What you'll bring: 
• In depth experience coaching and leading junior data scientists within a senior data science role. 
• Demonstrable experience of developing complex AI projects with minimal supervision, working in line with best practices. 
• Working knowledge of extracting business value from data science methods using both quantitative and qualitative metrics. 
• Strong mathematical and statistical background. 
• Deep knowledge of Python and data science packages such as Scikit learn, Keras, Tensor flow, and PySpark. 
• Experience and understanding of mixed technical teams such as engineering, architects, business analysts. 
• Familiar with MLOps industry best practices. 
• Good stakeholder communication skills with proven ability to translate complex scientific findings to non-technical stakeholders. 
• Understanding of the financial industry, in particular insurance, would be advantageous. 

If this sounds like you, please make an application and we'll be in touch.





Read the full job description here
https://click.totaljobsmail.com/f/a/GGvHi7K3K-vuTq2nbZeR2A~~/AAAmIgA~~~

Top skills
You're a great fit for this role if you have the following skills:
scikit-learn - Data Science - Machine learning - Spark Python API - Tensorflow -

Lead Data Scientist
Location: Milton Keynes
Salary: Up to £80,000 pa
Work Type: Full Time - Hybrid (3 days in office)
La Fosse is proud to partner with a rapidly growing international company operating in the retail and service sectors. The organisation is undergoing a digital transformation and is seeking a Lead Data Scientist to drive innovation and unlock the value of their data.
As a Lead Data Scientist, you'll work with diverse datasets, develop machine learning models, and deliver actionable insights to optimise business performance and operations.
Key Responsibilities:
Building hypotheses and validating their business impact.
Developing machine learning models and optimisation pipelines.
Translating technical data into actionable recommendations for stakeholders.
Designing interactive dashboards using Power BI to visualise real-time insights.
Collaborating with the Data Engineering team to create scalable data solutions.

Core Technical Skills:
3+ years of experience in data science/advanced analytics or machine learning role.
Strong programming skills in Python; familiarity with Azure and Power BI is essential.
Experience in regression analysis, classification, clustering, and feature engineering.
Proven ability to deliver high-impact insights and present to senior stakeholders.

Benefits:
Competitive salary up to £80,000
Hybrid working (3 days in office)
Generous annual leave

N.B: Unfortunately, visa sponsorship is unavailable for this role.

body:
Hello Divyaprakash,

We recommend this job for you. Take a look and see if you want to apply.




Lead Data Scientist
Xcede UK
UK Permanent £90000.00 - £110000.00 per annum 
 1 day ago

https://click.totaljobsmail.com/f/a/OugR6hAufXG_D_GT6HwAxw~~/AAAmIgA~



Lead Data Scientist
Up to £110,000
Remote - Visit to office once or twice a month
OVERVIEW
My Client is a Leading Insurance company hiring for a Data Science Lead to join their strong team and spearhead the Data Science function! You will be responsible for building production level Machine Learning models, working closely with the Data Engineering & Software Engineering teams and taking ownership over Data Science within the business. Your responsibilities as a Lead Data Scientist will include but not be limited to:
You will be responsible for developing, testing, and deploying a range of projects and predictive solutions
Lead and coach a Data Science function to deliver complex value-add activities
Regular delivery of data science projects - both large and small
Create explanatory models to analyse the correlation between pricing and other relevant business factors
Work closely with and help mentor some of the more junior members within the Data team.
Engage with senior business stakeholders

YOUR SKILLS & EXPERIENCE
A successful Lead Data Scientist will have the following:
Degree in STEM subject
Strong coding skills in Python and good understanding of software engineering best practices
Proven leadership/mentorship and management
Experience working end to end, deploying own models
Experience with Spark/Databricks is highly desirable
Experience deploying ML at scale via APIs
Strong experience with MLOps

Unfortunately no sponsorship is provided for this role

subject: Our recommendation: Lead Data Scientist – Bristol
body:
Hello Divyaprakash,

We recommend this job for you. Take a look and see if you want to apply.




Lead Data Scientist – Bristol
Datatech Analytics
Bristol, Avon Permanent Competitive annual salary of up to £90,000 dependent on experience 
 14 days ago

https://click.totaljobsmail.com/f/a/cU2c_kj2gKu3qS3H5dr9gA~~/AAAmIgA~



Lead Data Scientist - ML & AI projects
Competitive annual salary of up to £90,000 dependent on experience 
Hybrid working - Bristol office base (currently 2 days in office but expected to move to 3)
Ref J12883

Unfortunately, no sponsorship available with this client so full UK working rights required

Our client is seeking to recruit a new Lead Data Scientist to lead data science initiatives and drive innovation in the healthcare industry. You'll have the opportunity to leverage your expertise in data analysis and machine learning within our dynamic and forward-thinking team, to shape the future of healthcare. If you're passionate about making a real impact and are ready to lead a team of talented data scientists, we want to hear from you.

What you'll be doing: 
• Lead a relatively small team of data scientists in developing and implementing advanced data analytics, machine learning and traditional and generative AI solutions, to address complex challenges in healthcare. 
• Collaborate with cross-functional teams to identify business opportunities, define data science strategies, and drive the development of innovative products and services. 
• Oversee the end-to-end process of data collection, pre-processing, analysis, and model development to derive actionable insights and improve decision-making. 
• Drive the development and deployment of scalable and efficient machine learning models and algorithms to enhance healthcare services and optimize business operations. 
• Mentor and coach junior data scientists, fostering a culture of continuous learning, innovation, and excellence in data science practices.

What you'll bring: 
• In depth experience coaching and leading junior data scientists within a senior data science role. 
• Demonstrable experience of developing complex AI projects with minimal supervision, working in line with best practices. 
• Working knowledge of extracting business value from data science methods using both quantitative and qualitative metrics. 
• Strong mathematical and statistical background. 
• Deep knowledge of Python and data science packages such as Scikit learn, Keras, Tensor flow, and PySpark. 
• Experience and understanding of mixed technical teams such as engineering, architects, business analysts. 
• Familiar with MLOps industry best practices. 
• Good stakeholder communication skills with proven ability to translate complex scientific findings to non-technical stakeholders. 
• Understanding of the financial industry, in particular insurance, would be advantageous. 

If this sounds like you, please make an application and we'll be in touch.

subject: My Thanksgiving sale is now on!
body:
New Promotional Announcement

Hi Divyaprakash, an announcement has been made from Phillip, instructor of PL-300 certification prep: Microsoft Power BI Data Analyst.

Hello everyone, and thank you for joining me in the above course.

There is 1½ months left in 2024. What do you want to learn before the end of the year?

  • Is it SQL Server: T-SQL, SSAS, SSIS, or maybe SSRS? What about Azure Database Administration?

  • What about Reporting Software? Tableau, Power BI, Fabric, or Crystal Reports?

  • Do you want to learn a new skill at the Fundamental level, or higher? Microsoft Azure, Security, Programming or Databases?

  • How about Power Platform: Power Apps, Power Automate, Power BI and more?

  • Is it Microsoft Office: Word, Excel, PowerPoint or Access?

  • Or do you want a shorter course, to learn one particular skill?

It's perfectly achievable to learn one of these (or more than one) in the next few months. Why not go for it?

My Thanksgiving sale is now on. Udemy have been having mini-sales, but the prices they have been charging are higher than I can offer you in this sale. Unfortunately, Udemy has changed the voucher system, so I can no longer give you a specific price.

However, I can say that, if you click on any of the links in the below email, or use the voucher code VOUCHER202411, you will get “the lowest price Udemy would offer any student for this course”. In other words, you will not get a better price for my courses than by using the links in this email.


This includes my brand new course on SQL Server SSAS (Tabular model).


The only way you will find out how little all my courses cost is by clicking on the below links. But hurry - this offer ends on Monday.

Sounds interesting? Here’s some details about each course:

----

REPORTING COURSES

Power BI: PL-300 Microsoft Power BI Data Analyst

https://www.udemy.com/course/70-778-analyzing-and-visualizing-data-with-power-bi/?couponCode=VOUCHER202411

Power BI is one of the most requested reporting tools that are requested in the job market, and the ability to being able to use it now could be very useful for your current work, and your next job hunt.

This course comes in four parts:

  • Part 1 - Creating Visualizations (also known as Visualize the Data, and Analyze the Data)

  • Part 2 - Get and Transform Data (also known as Prepare the Data), using the DAX language

  • Part 3 - Refining the model (also known as Model the Data), using the M language

  • Part 4 - Power BI Service

At the end of the course, you will be proficient in Power BI. And with a bit of practice, you could also go for the official Microsoft PL-300 exam - wouldn’t that certificate look good on your CV or resume? And if you are an American college student, you might even get college credit for passing that exam.


Power BI and Fabric: DP-600 Fabric Analytics Engineer Associate

https://www.udemy.com/course/dp-600-implementing-analytics-solutions-using-microsoft-fabric/?couponCode=VOUCHER202411

Our DP-600 course develops on the skills you have learned in the PL-300 Power BI course, with advanced data modelling and Microsoft Fabric for data analysts.

  • Part 1 - Advanced data modelling. We'll go further into semantic models and relationships and learn new DAX formulas.

  • Part 2 - Microsoft Fabric. This can hold the data online which you can then use in the Power BI Service. We'll load data and query it using SQL.

Tableau: Data Analyst and Desktop Specialist Associate certification

https://www.udemy.com/course/tableau-2018-tableau-10-qualified-associate-certification/?couponCode=VOUCHER202411

In this course, we’ll look at how to create Tableau visualisations (vizzes), dashboards and stories. We'll create maps, hierarchies, groups and sets, and all sorts of chart types. We'll enhance our charts with reference lines and bands, and extend our data analysis with trends and forecasting. We'll add formula calculations, quick table calculations, and LOD calculations. Finally, we investigate advanced data connections and mapping, together with some things you can do in the full Tableau Creator.

This course has been updated this month in line with the new Data Analyst certification, as well as supporting the Desktop Specialist certification. With some practice, you can then enter these certifications and, once earned, add them to your CV or resume.


Oracle SQL: 1Z0-171 Learn Oracle SQL and prepare for the Certified Associate certification

https://www.udemy.com/course/1z0-171-oracle-database-23ai-sql-associate/?couponCode=VOUCHER202411

We start off this course by looking at the six principal clauses of the SELECT statement: SELECT, FROM, WHERE, GROUP BY, HAVING and ORDER BY. We’ll then expand this by creating views and sub queries, combining tables together using JOINs, self-JOINs and UNION, plus much more.

By the end of this course you could, with some practice, enter into the Oracle 1Z0-171 exam and earn an official Oracle certification.


Crystal Reports: An Introduction

https://www.udemy.com/course/crystal-reports-an-introduction/?couponCode=VOUCHER202411

This course is separated into 7 levels, each getting progressively more deeper into Crystal Reports. They are:

1. Creating your first report,

2. Adding grouping, sorting and filtering, also known as Selecting.

3. Formatting,

4. Adding user interaction through parameters,

5. Graphs and charts,

6. Subreports, and

7. Formulas.

By the end, you will be able to develop your own reports, and start to explore other people's.

----

SHORTER AZURE AND GANTT CHART COURSES (3 hours or less)

Develop generative AI solutions with Azure OpenAI Service.

https://www.udemy.com/course/microsoft-applied-skills-develop-generative-ai-solutions-azure-openai/?couponCode=VOUCHER202411

Generate natural language responses, apply prompt engineering techniques and generate and improve code using an Azure OpenAI resource, and the portal, C# or Python. You’ll also use OpenAI on your own data, and generate images with DALL-E.


Build an Azure AI Vision solution

https://www.udemy.com/course/microsoft-applied-skills-build-an-azure-ai-vision-solution/?couponCode=VOUCHER202411

This allows you to use Artificial Intelligence to analyse images, create captions, retrieve text, tag images, and much more.


Create an intelligent document processing solution with Azure AI Document Intelligence.

https://www.udemy.com/course/microsoft-applied-skills-azure-ai-document-intelligence/?couponCode=VOUCHER202411

Read text from images (OCR - Optical Character Recognition), using general-purpose models, and other models such as those designed especially to read invoices.


Build a natural language processing solution with Azure AI Language.

https://www.udemy.com/course/microsoft-applied-skills-azure-ai-language/?couponCode=VOUCHER202411

Analyse text, identifying the language, extracting key phrases, recognise entities (such as dates, addresses, recipients and more) and sentiment, and more.


Azure Files and Azure Blob Storage.

https://www.udemy.com/course/microsoft-applied-skills-azure-files-and-azure-blob-storage/?couponCode=VOUCHER202411

Store your images and files in the cloud using Azure Storage, and then secure them so that only permitted people can access them.


Project Management: Gantt Charts in an hour.

https://www.udemy.com/course/project-management-gantt-charts-in-an-hour/?couponCode=VOUCHER202411

You'll learn how to plan and build Gantt charts, from defining project scope to breaking down tasks and milestones, with creating relationships between tasks and resource management.


---

T-SQL: SQL Server Essentials in an hour: The SELECT statement

https://www.udemy.com/sql-server-essentials-in-an-hour-the-select-statement/?couponCode=VOUCHER202411

Only got an hour to spare? No problem - get to grips with the SELECT statement - SELECT, FROM, WHERE, GROUP BY, HAVING and ORDER BY. We'll then look at saving your code using both views and procedures.

---

T-SQL: Sessions 1-7 in one course: Querying Microsoft SQL Server (SQL code)

https://www.udemy.com/70-461-session-2-querying-microsoft-sql-server-2012/?couponCode=VOUCHER202411

In the first 7 hours of this course, you can go from no knowledge in SQL to writing SELECT statements using all 6 of the main clauses, including JOINing multiple tables together.

We'll now use that knowledge in the remaining 22 hours of this course to create views, which enable us to store these SELECT queries for future use, and triggers. We'll have a look at constraints, MERGEing, creating procedures, aggregating queries, creating sub-queries, using XML and JSON, and much, much more.

----

T-SQL: Database Fundamentals

https://www.udemy.com/course/98-364-database-fundamentals-microsoft-sql-server/?couponCode=VOUCHER202411

Want to learn T-SQL, but want something a bit shorter? In this 8½ hour course, you’ll learn all of the SELECT statement’s main clauses, as well as how to create constraints, views, procedures, functions, triggers and more.

----

SQL code: SQL for Microsoft Access

https://www.udemy.com/sql-for-microsoft-access-2007-to-2016/?couponCode=VOUCHER202411

Do you use Microsoft Access instead of SQL Server? Do you want to learn how to write more advanced queries in Access? And do you want your queries to be portable into both SQL Server and Access?

In this course learn how to:

  • Write SQL code, using the six SELECT clauses.

  • Use functions and formulas in your SELECT statements.

  • Create JOINs between tables and queries, including more complex joins which cannot be created using the graphical interface.

  • Write action queries and cross-queries.

----

DBA: SQL Server Database Administration (DBA)

https://www.udemy.com/70-462-sql-server-database-administration-dba/?couponCode=VOUCHER202411

In this course we'll start by downloading a demonstration database, learning how to backup and restore this database, and what recovery models are appropriate for your databases, to enable you to offer Point in Time recovery.

We'll manage logins and server roles, so you can control who gets access to what data, implement and maintain indexes, improving the speed of your queries, and import and export data. We'll look at managing SQL Server Agent, so you can automate routine tasks and be alerted to problems, we'll manage and configure databases, and look at compression, both of which aid with administrating big databases. And much more.

The course will take around 10 hours to complete, but completing this will enable you to versed in Database Administration tasks, giving you hands-on experience.

----

Azure DBA: DP-300 Administering Relational Databases

https://www.udemy.com/course/dp-300-administering-relational-databases-azure-dba/?couponCode=VOUCHER202411

In this course we’ll be looking at how to administrate Azure SQL Database, Azure SQL Managed Instance, and SQL Server on Azure Virtual Machines.

In this course, learn how to:

  • Plan and implement data platform resources,

  • Implement a secure environment,

  • Monitor and optimize operational resources,

  • Optimize query performance,

  • Perform automation of tasks,

  • Plan and implement a High Availability and Disaster Recovery (HADR) environment, and

  • Perform administration by using T-SQL.

By the end of this course, you should be confident with administering relational databases on Azure – and you could even enter the DP-300 Microsoft exam and (if you pass) get an official Microsoft certification. Wouldn’t that look good on your CV or resume?

----

SSAS MDX: SQL Server SSAS (Multidimensional MDX) - an Introduction

https://www.udemy.com/sql-server-ssas-multidimensional-mdx-an-introduction/?couponCode=VOUCHER202411

This course is designed for the complete beginner in Multidimensional cubes, or someone who wants to refresh their memory. We’ll create a cube to start with from an ordinary database, and then I’ll ask you to create one from a special database known as a Data Warehouse. We’ll export our cube into SQL Server Management Studio and SSRS. The second part of the course is all about querying this database using the MDX language.

----

SSAS Tabular: Microsoft SSAS (Tabular DAX model) - NEW COURSE

https://www.udemy.com/microsoft-powerpivot-and-ssas-tabular-dax-model/?couponCode=VOUCHER202411

In this course, you'll create your first tabular analysis in just a few minutes. After this introduction, we'll go into some detail into SQL Server’s SSAS - the initial data, and the various options that are available to you. We will go into advanced options that most people don't even know about, but which are very useful.

Then we'll develop DAX formulas, to further extend the model. A lot of DAX formulas are based on Excel, but there are several additional formulas as well.

By the end, you will be an Expert user of the Tabular version of SSAS, able to create reliable analyses in Excel and elsewhere which are able to be drilled-down quickly, and you'll be able to help others with their data analysis.

----

SSRS: Microsoft SQL Server Reporting Services (SSRS)

https://www.udemy.com/microsoft-sql-server-reporting-services-ssrs/?couponCode=VOUCHER202411

In this course, we'll create various reports, developing our skills bit by bit. As part of designing a report, we will:

  • Select report components (matrix, table, chart and other data visualisation component),

  • Identify the data source and parameters,

  • Design a grouping structure, and

  • Create drilldown reports and drillthrough reports.

We'll look closely at implementing a report layout and interactivity in a report. By the end of this course, you should be confident in creating your own reports in SSRS.

----

SSIS: SQL Server Integration Services (SSIS) - An Introduction

https://www.udemy.com/sql-server-ssis-an-introduction/?couponCode=VOUCHER202411

What is SSIS? It’s a way to automate in the importing and exporting and data – or ETL: extract, transform and load. It’s a very visual part of SSIS, using tasks, components and flowcharts, so it’s easy to learn the basics of it.

We’ll start by extracting some data, and then loading it into another table. I’ll take nice as slow as we start to introduce transformations, such as aggregation, conditional split, merging and auditing. There’ll be plenty of practice activities too, so you can get to practice your new-found skills.

----

FUNDAMENTAL LEVEL…OR ABOVE

Programming

In these courses, we will look at:

  • Core programming fundamentals, such as decision structures, repetition and error handling,

  • Object-oriented programming fundamentals, such as classes, inheritance, polymorphism and encapsulation,

  • General software development fundamentals: application life cycle management, application specifications, and algorithms and data structures,

  • Web applications fundamentals: web page development, Microsoft ASP NET web application development, web hosting and web services,

  • Desktop application fundamentals, namely Windows apps, console-based applications and Windows Services, and

  • Databases fundamentals, including query methods and database connection methods.

To learn about programming:

  • For C#, please go to https://www.udemy.com/course/98-361-software-development-fundamentals-using-c-sharp/?couponCode=VOUCHER202411

  • For VB Net, please go to https://www.udemy.com/course/98-361-software-development-fundamentals-using-vb-net-visual-basic-net/?couponCode=VOUCHER202411

----

Databases

https://www.udemy.com/course/98-364-database-fundamentals-microsoft-sql-server/?couponCode=VOUCHER202411

In this course, we will look at how to:

  • Create tables in a database, normalize the tables, and ALTER columns in the table.

  • know what data type to use in various situations.

  • retrieve data using SELECT, FROM, WHERE, GROUP BY, HAVING and ORDER BY.

  • JOIN two tables together, finding missing data.

  • INSERT new data, UPDATE and DELETE existing data, and export data INTO a new table.

  • Create constraints, views, procedures and triggers

  • Create backups and restore data, and investigate security

----

AZURE

Microsoft Azure - Generally (AZ-900)

https://www.udemy.com/course/az-900-microsoft-azure-fundamentals-exam-preparation/?couponCode=VOUCHER202411

In the first of my Azure courses, we will look at Azure generally:

  • Cloud concepts, core Azure services, and core solutions and management tools on Azure,

  • General Security and network security features,

  • Identity, governance, privacy, and compliance features, and

  • Azure cost management and Service Level Agreements.

----

Microsoft Azure - Data (DP-900)

https://www.udemy.com/course/dp-900-microsoft-azure-data-fundamentals-course/?couponCode=VOUCHER202411

In the second of my Azure courses, you can concentrate on data and databases in Azure, with a little bit of Power BI as well:

  • Understand types of core data workloads and data analytics core concepts,

  • Understand how to work with relational data on Azure, including Azure SQL Database and Managed Instance,

  • Understand how to work with non-relational data on Azure, including Cosmos DB APIs, Table, Blob and File storage,

  • Describe analytics workloads, including data warehouses, data ingestion and processing on Azure, and

  • Describe data visualization in Microsoft Power BI, including reports and dashboards.

----

Microsoft Azure and Microsoft 365 - Microsoft Security, Compliance and Identity Fundamentals (SC-900)

https://www.udemy.com/course/sc-900-microsoft-security-complianceidentity-fundamentals/?couponCode=VOUCHER202411

In the third of my Azure courses, which also includes Microsoft 365, we will look at:

  • Describe the concepts of security, compliance, and identity,

  • Describe the capabilities of Microsoft identity and access management solutions,

  • Describe the capabilities of Microsoft security solutions, and

  • Describe the capabilities of Microsoft compliance solutions.

----

Power Platform - Power BI, Power Apps, Power Automate and more (PL-900, PL-100, PL-200 and PL-400)

This course is an introduction to the Power Platform:

  • Describe the business value of Microsoft's Power Platform,

  • Identify the Core Components of Power Platform, including Dataverse (CDS), Connectors and AI Builder, and

  • Demonstrate the capabilities of Power BI, Power Apps, Power Automate and Power Virtual Agents.

PL-900: To learn about the Power Platform at the Foundation level, which looks at the theory of the Power Platform, please go to https://www.udemy.com/course/pl-900-microsoft-power-platform-fundamentals-r/?couponCode=VOUCHER202411

PL-200 Part 1: To learn about the Power Platform at a more advanced and practical level, please go to https://www.udemy.com/course/pl-100-microsoft-power-platform-app-maker-ms/?couponCode=VOUCHER202411

PL-200 Part 2: To build on what you have learnt in the Part 1 course, have a look at my Part 2 course by going to https://www.udemy.com/course/pl-200-microsoft-power-platform-functional-consultant-course/?couponCode=VOUCHER202411

PL-400: To extend the Power Platform user experience and platform using JavaScript/TypeScript and C#, have a look at my PL-400 course by going to https://www.udemy.com/course/pl-400-microsoft-power-platform-developer-course/?couponCode=VOUCHER202411

----

Create processes using Power Automate

https://www.udemy.com/course/microsoft-applied-skills-processes-using-power-automate/?couponCode=VOUCHER202411

Create automated processes, for when new data arrives, on a timetable, or when you need it. Create actions based on that data, approvals for requests for leave, and implement conditional logic.

----

Create canvas apps with Power Apps

https://www.udemy.com/course/microsoft-applied-skills-create-canvas-apps-with-power-apps/?couponCode=VOUCHER202411

Create a 3-screen app in the cloud, upload your data, and use the app to add new and modify existing data.

----

Create and manage model-driven apps with Power Apps and Dataverse

https://www.udemy.com/course/microsoft-applied-skills-create-model-driven-power-apps-and-dataverse/?couponCode=VOUCHER202411

Create a model-driven app, using Dataverse tables, forms and views in a Dataverse solution.

----

Dynamics 365 CRM (MB-910)

https://www.udemy.com/course/mb-910-microsoft-dynamics-365-fundamentals-crm-v/?couponCode=VOUCHER202411

In this Fundamentals course, we’ll look at Dynamics 365 Marketing, Sales, Customer Service and Field Service. We’ll get free trials of the various Dynamics 365 apps, so you can try it on your computer.

----

MICROSOFT OFFICE

Microsoft Office for PC

Want to be certified in Microsoft Office? In this course, you'll learn all of the requirements of the MO-100, MO-200 and MO-300 exams. That's Word, Excel and PowerPoint all in the one course – all of the requirements of the Microsoft Office Specialist: Associate certification.

https://www.udemy.com/course/microsoft-office-specialist-associate-word-mo-100-excel-mo-200-mo-300/?couponCode=VOUCHER202411

----

My Excel 1 and 2 courses each are about 11 hours long, and take you from absolute beginner to an Expert. You could (and others have) take a Microsoft Excel Expert exam, and with other exams, you could get an official Office Expert or Office Master certification - how would that look on your resume or CV?

There are plenty of practice activities as you go, so you can be sure that you are learning.

Excel 1 PC (MO-210 exam)

https://www.udemy.com/course/mo-210-microsoft-excel-microsoft-365-apps/?couponCode=VOUCHER202411

Excel 2 PC (MO-211 exam - more advanced)

https://www.udemy.com/course/mo-211-microsoft-excel-expert-microsoft-365-apps/?couponCode=VOUCHER202411

---

Or maybe you want to learn more about PivotTables. There is a lot of functionality that others don't know about, but you could learn very quickly.

The PC version of this course also includes the very useful Get and Transform (Power Query) and Power Pivot – something every Excel expert should know.

Excel 3 PC (PivotTables, Power Query and Power Pivot)

https://www.udemy.com/master-pivot-tables-introduction-and-masterclass/?couponCode=VOUCHER202411

---

Or how about taking your first steps in Visual Basic for Applications, and being able to automate your applications?

Excel 4 PC (VBA)

https://www.udemy.com/excel-vba-visual-basic-for-applications-an-introduction/?couponCode=VOUCHER202411

---

Want more? Here's Word, PowerPoint and Access:

Microsoft Word 1

https://www.udemy.com/77-418-session-1improve-ms-word-skills-to-certificate-level/?couponCode=VOUCHER202411

Microsoft Word 2

https://www.udemy.com/microsoft-word-from-intermediate-to-expert-certification/?couponCode=VOUCHER202411

Microsoft Access Beginner to Specialist (Intermediate) Level

https://www.udemy.com/microsoft-access-beginner-to-specialist-intermediate-level/?couponCode=VOUCHER202411

SQL for Microsoft Access

https://www.udemy.com/sql-for-microsoft-access-2007-to-2016/?couponCode=VOUCHER202411

----

Microsoft Office for Mac

Got a Mac? Have a look at Microsoft Excel for Mac.

Excel Mac 1

https://www.udemy.com/microsoft-excel-go-from-beginner-to-specialist-certificate/?couponCode=VOUCHER202411

Excel Mac 2 (more advanced)

https://www.udemy.com/microsoft-excel-for-mac-2-intermediate-to-expert-advanced/?couponCode=VOUCHER202411

Excel Mac 3 (PivotTables)

https://www.udemy.com/excel-2016-for-mac-3-pivot-tables-intro-masterclass/?couponCode=VOUCHER202411

Excel Mac 4 (VBA)

https://www.udemy.com/microsoft-excel-2016-mac-4-vba-macros-for-excel-an-intro/?couponCode=VOUCHER202411

----

I hope that you found this email interesting, and that you will be able to develop your skills, and even take one or more official Microsoft certifications to add to your CV or resume.

Thank you very much for reading this - I hope to see you in these courses. Any problems, let me know. And keep learning.

Phillip

Delivered by Udemy 600 Harrison Street, 3rd Floor, San Francisco, CA 94107. You may unsubscribe if you prefer not to receive messages like these. If something isn't right, please report abuse.

Your update from Akixi

subject: Our recommendation: Lead Data Scientist - ML & AI projects – Kent
body:
Hello Divyaprakash,

We recommend this job for you. Take a look and see if you want to apply.




Lead Data Scientist - ML & AI projects – Kent
Datatech Analytics
Tunbridge Wells, Kent Permanent Competitive annual salary of up to £90,000 dependent on experience 
 1 day ago

https://click.totaljobsmail.com/f/a/23b2qXK_uOSIsgC_sRTRIQ~~/AAAmIgA~-jwLWdTGj2OUhlyZGl2eWFwcmFrYXNoNzhAZ21haWwuY29tWAQAAAAG



Lead Data Scientist - ML & AI projects
Competitive annual salary of up to £90,000 dependent on experience 
Hybrid working - West Kent office base (currently 2 days in office but expected to move to 3)
Ref J12882

Unfortunately, no sponsorship available with this client so full UK working rights required

Our client is seeking to recruit a new Lead Data Scientist to lead data science initiatives and drive innovation in the healthcare industry. You'll have the opportunity to leverage your expertise in data analysis and machine learning within our dynamic and forward-thinking team, to shape the future of healthcare. If you're passionate about making a real impact and are ready to lead a team of talented data scientists, we want to hear from you.

What you'll be doing: 
• Lead a relatively small team of data scientists in developing and implementing advanced data analytics, machine learning and traditional and generative AI solutions, to address complex challenges in healthcare. 
• Collaborate with cross-functional teams to identify business opportunities, define data science strategies, and drive the development of innovative products and services. 
• Oversee the end-to-end process of data collection, pre-processing, analysis, and model development to derive actionable insights and improve decision-making. 
• Drive the development and deployment of scalable and efficient machine learning models and algorithms to enhance healthcare services and optimize business operations. 
• Mentor and coach junior data scientists, fostering a culture of continuous learning, innovation, and excellence in data science practices.

What you'll bring: 
• In depth experience coaching and leading junior data scientists within a senior data science role. 
• Demonstrable experience of developing complex AI projects with minimal supervision, working in line with best practices. 
• Working knowledge of extracting business value from data science methods using both quantitative and qualitative metrics. 
• Strong mathematical and statistical background. 
• Deep knowledge of Python and data science packages such as Scikit learn, Keras, Tensor flow, and PySpark. 
• Experience and understanding of mixed technical teams such as engineering, architects, business analysts. 
• Familiar with MLOps industry best practices. 
• Good stakeholder communication skills with proven ability to translate complex scientific findings to non-technical stakeholders. 
• Understanding of the financial industry, in particular insurance, would be advantageous. 

If this sounds like you, please make an application and we'll be in touch.





Read the full job description here
https://click.totaljobsmail.com/f/a/gqZPTW3_bEUEjGGggEtjag~~/AAAmIgA~~~

Top skills
You're a great fit for this role if you have the following skills:
scikit-learn - Data Science - Machine learning - Spark Python API - Tensorflow -

subject: Our recommendation: Prophet Actuary
body:
Hello Divyaprakash,

We recommend this job for you. Take a look and see if you want to apply.




Prophet Actuary
Merje
London Permanent £80k - 90k per year 
 20 days ago

https://click.totaljobsmail.com/f/a/sC3uvCDETI6Bmk4I-h6Sew~~/AAAmIgA~



MERJE are supporting a Life Insurance client with the hire of a Prophet Modelling Actuary.
We're expecting candidates to be around the Nearly or Newly (including those Post Qualified) level. Applicants must have extensive knowledge and specialised in Actuarial model development using Prophet libraries.
This role will be focusing on both the coding of the model as well as model development.
This is a permanent UK based role with hybrid/flexible working. 2 days a week in the office is expected and all applicants must be eligible to work in the UK.

subject: Confirmation of your application to 9fin
body:
Hi Divyaprakash,
Thank you for taking the time to apply to the ML Applied Scientist role
here at 9fin.
We appreciate your interest and are thrilled you'd like to join us. We
understand that applying for a new job can be exciting and scary, and we
want to assure you that your application is important to us. Our Talent
team is currently reviewing applications, and we are carefully considering
each candidate's qualifications and experiences.
Here's what you can expect moving forward:

   1. Application review: Our team will thoroughly review your application
   to assess your qualifications and alignment with the role's requirements.
   This process may take a bit of time as we aim to give every application the
   attention it deserves.
   2. Communication: We will keep you informed about the progress of your
   application. If your background matches what we are looking for, we will
   contact you to discuss the next steps. While we aim to provide updates in a
   timely manner, please understand that the volume of applications we receive
   might lead to slight delays here.
   3. Feedback: We understand that feedback is valuable for personal and
   professional growth. While we may not be able to provide detailed feedback
   for every application, we will do our best to offer insights if your
   application reaches an advanced stage of consideration.

In the meantime, we encourage you to learn more about 9fin and our mission
by taking a look at our *careers page*
<https://www.notion.so/9fin/Careers-at-9fin-7816c57be574418daea2b9f55355034c>
and *website* <https://9fin.com/about>, which will help you gain a better
understanding of our culture, values and the work we do.
Thanks you once again for applying for a career at 9fin. We value your
interest and are excited to learn more about you.
Warm regards,
The 9fin Talent Team
