subject: Universal-2 Nominated! PLUS Smarter Speech AI Tools to Build With
body:
( # )Hey 👋, this weekly update contains the latest info on our new product features, tutorials, and our community.

Join Us On Discord ( https://discord.gg/CEqt6x2YPK )

🏆 Universal-2 Nominated for Product Hunt's 2024 Golden Kitty Awards! ( https://www.producthunt.com/golden-kitty-awards/data-data-security-2?v=2 )

We’re excited to share that Universal-2 ( https://www.assemblyai.com/universal-2?utm_source=email&utm_medium=newsletter&utm_campaign=newsletter_67 ) and Universal-1 ( https://www.assemblyai.com/blog/announcing-universal-1-speech-recognition-model/?utm_source=email&utm_medium=newsletter&utm_campaign=newsletter_67 ), the best-in-class speech-to-text models, have
been nominated for Product Hunt's 2024 Golden Kitty Awards in the Data & Data Security category! These models deliver unmatched transcription accuracy, capturing the nuances of diverse languages, accents, and real-world audio with ease, while providing developers with reliable and scalable solutions for their projects.

 

Check out this year's nominees here ( https://www.producthunt.com/golden-kitty-awards/data-data-security-2?v=2 ), and don’t miss the chance to support your favorites. Voting ends Sunday, January 26th! 🚀

Build with AssemblyAI’s Conversational Intelligence
Models ( https://www.assemblyai.com/docs/audio-intelligence?utm_source=email&utm_medium=newsletter&utm_campaign=newsletter_67 )

Take your applications built on spoken data to the next level with our conversational intelligence models ( https://www.assemblyai.com/docs/audio-intelligence?utm_source=email&utm_medium=newsletter&utm_campaign=newsletter_67 ) that provide deeper insights and better processing of your spoken data. These models are designed to extract actionable information, analyze conversations, and enhance the functionality of your solutions:

* 🗣️ Speaker Diarization ( https://www.assemblyai.com/docs/speech-to-text/speaker-diarization?utm_source=email&utm_medium=newsletter&utm_campaign=newsletter_67 ): Identify and separate speakers in multi-speaker audio.
*
✂️ Summarization ( https://www.assemblyai.com/docs/audio-intelligence/summarization?utm_source=email&utm_medium=newsletter&utm_campaign=newsletter_67 ): Generate concise and meaningful summaries of long-form audio content.
*
🚨 Content Moderation ( https://www.assemblyai.com/docs/audio-intelligence/content-moderation?utm_source=email&utm_medium=newsletter&utm_campaign=newsletter_67 ): Automatically detect and flag inappropriate or sensitive content.
*
😊 Sentiment Analysis ( https://www.assemblyai.com/docs/audio-intelligence/sentiment-analysis?utm_source=email&utm_medium=newsletter&utm_campaign=newsletter_67 ): Evaluate the tone and emotions within a conversation for deeper understanding.
*
🏷️ Entity Detection ( https://www.assemblyai.com/docs/audio-intelligence/entity-detection?utm_source=email&utm_medium=newsletter&utm_campaign=newsletter_67 ): Extract key entities like names, dates, and locations to surface critical details.

Visit our documentation ( https://www.assemblyai.com/docs?utm_source=email&utm_medium=newsletter&utm_campaign=newsletter_67 ) to integrate these models into your apps today.

Fresh From Our Blog ( https://www.assemblyai.com/blog/?utm_source=email&utm_medium=newsletter&utm_campaign=newsletter_67 )

How to build a LiveKit app with real-time Speech-to-Text ( https://www.assemblyai.com/blog/livekit-realtime-speech-to-text/?utm_source=email&utm_medium=newsletter&utm_campaign=newsletter_67 )

LiveKit allows you to build real-time audio and video applications - learn how to add real-time Speech-to-Text to your LiveKit application in this tutorial. Read more>> ( https://www.assemblyai.com/blog/livekit-realtime-speech-to-text/?utm_source=email&utm_medium=newsletter&utm_campaign=newsletter_67 )

Speech recognition in the browser using Web Speech API ( https://www.assemblyai.com/blog/speech-recognition-javascript-web-speech-api/?utm_source=email&utm_medium=newsletter&utm_campaign=newsletter_67 )

Learn how to set up speech recognition in your browser using the Web Speech API and JavaScript. Read more>> ( https://www.assemblyai.com/blog/speech-recognition-javascript-web-speech-api/?utm_source=email&utm_medium=newsletter&utm_campaign=newsletter_67 )

Build a Real-Time AI Voice Bot Using Python, AssemblyAI, and ElevenLabs ( https://www.assemblyai.com/blog/real-time-ai-voice-bot-python/?utm_source=email&utm_medium=newsletter&utm_campaign=newsletter_67 )

Build a real-time AI voice bot using Python, AssemblyAI, OpenAI, and ElevenLabs for transcription, intelligent responses, and voice synthesis. Read more>> ( https://www.assemblyai.com/blog/real-time-ai-voice-bot-python/?utm_source=email&utm_medium=newsletter&utm_campaign=newsletter_67 )

Our Trending YouTube Tutorials ( https://www.youtube.com/@AssemblyAI )

ratio ( https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QP4HsdEPd-M )
Build An AI Chat Bot In Java | Real-Time Prompting ( https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QP4HsdEPd-M )

Learn how to create an AI chat bot in Java that accepts real-time audio input as prompts by using AssemblyAI for real-time speech-to-text transcription and LeMUR.

ratio ( https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZduW0N31JuE )
Build an AI Voice Translator: Keep Your Voice in Any Language! (Python + Gradio Tutorial) ( https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZduW0N31JuE )

Build a web-based voice-to-voice cloning app using Gradio, AssemblyAI for transcription and Elevenlabs for reading translated text in your own voice

ratio ( https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-w30hXPLtJk )
Speaker Diarization In Python - Transcription with Speaker Labels ( https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-w30hXPLtJk )

Explore how to use AssemblyAI for accurately identifying and labeling speakers in audio recordings. Learn how speaker diarization works, enabling you to distinguish "who spoke when" in conversations.

AssemblyAI.com ( https://www.assemblyai.com/?utm_source=email&utm_medium=newsletter&utm_campaign=newsletter_67 )
 YouTube ( https://www.youtube.com/c/AssemblyAI )
Twitter ( https://twitter.com/assemblyai )LinkedIn ( https://www.linkedin.com/company/assemblyai/ )Custom ( https://discord.gg/CEqt6x2YPK )TikTok ( https://www.tiktok.com/@assemblyai )
AssemblyAI builds on the latest state-of-the-art AI research to offer production-ready, scalable, and secure AI models through a simple API. You can use AssemblyAI to build AI-powered features in your audio and video products, making it easy to transcribe and understand speech at scale.

 

Join thousands of breakthrough startups and dozens of global enterprises and start building with AssemblyAI for mission-critical workloads.

subject: Our recommendation: Algorithm Development Lead
body:
Hello Divyaprakash,

We recommend this job for you. Take a look and see if you want to apply.



Algorithm Development Lead

Henderson Scott
Stevenage, Hertfordshire

Permanent

Up to £58000.00 per annum + Bonus, + Substantial Benefits

25 days ago





Apply Now
https://click.totaljobsmail.com/f/a/LxeUhZBOLTHqUfgNzcGeEw~~/AAAmIgA~


Algorithm Development Lead
 Location: Stevenage
 Salary: Circa £58,000, depending on experience

About the Role
 We are seeking an Algorithm Development Lead to join our Guidance, Control, and Navigation team. You will lead the development of advanced algorithms for next-generation weapon systems, contributing to all stages of the product lifecycle. This role offers the opportunity to steer technical activities, grow your team, and build strong partnerships with stakeholders and customers.
 Your Responsibilities
Lead the Stevenage algorithm development team and shape its technical direction.
Develop and maintain onboard algorithms for guidance, control, and navigation systems.
Collaborate with multidisciplinary teams, including Simulation, Image Processing, and Systems Design.
Act as the key point of contact for partners and customers on algorithm-related activities.
Explore innovative technologies and their applications in complex systems.

What We're Looking For
Strong leadership and communication skills, with a collaborative and inspiring approach.
Experience in algorithm development and associated tools.
Background in a subject with mathematical content (e.g., Aerospace Engineering, Mathematics, Physics, Computer Science).
Knowledge of domains such as Guidance, Navigation, Control Systems, or Autonomous Systems is advantageous.
A degree qualification or equivalent experience; post-doctoral or industrial experience is beneficial.

What We Offer
Bonus: Up to £2,500, based on company performance.
Pension: Employer and employee contributions up to 14%.
Flexi Leave: Up to 15 additional days.
Parental Leave: Enhanced options for maternity, adoption, and shared parental leave.
Facilities: Subsidised meals, free car parking, and excellent on-site amenities.
Career Growth: Opportunities for training, development, and progression in a cutting-edge environment.

Eligibility
You must be a British citizen or hold dual UK nationality. Security clearance is required for this role.

Ready to Lead the Future of Algorithm Development?
 Apply now and play a pivotal role in delivering innovative solutions for next-generation systems.

Client Details
Our client is a Data & Analytics Company based in Central London. The role is hybrid and the team go to the office once or twice a week. The company was founded 5 years and you will be joining a rapidly growing team.
Description
Work on Greenfield projects
Write scaleable code in C#
Work closely with the Data team
Reduce technical debt
Drive the implementation of new technologies
Data structuring
Advanced Algorithms

Profile
Must haves:
Modern C#
AWS (Athena, ECS, Lambdas, Cloudwatch)
SQL
Kafka
Redis
Worked on large data sets

Nice to haves:
Degree in Maths or Data Science or similar
Worked in a gaming or gambling company

Job Offer
Discretionary bonus -
Pension contribution - pension scheme through The Nest. ER contribution of up to 4% of total salary.
Season ticket loan - interest free loan to all employees for the purpose of purchasing a season ticket.
Health care cover/gym membership - the option of either private health care cover or corporate gym membership.
Annual leave - 26 days annual leave and the usual bank holidays
Cycle to work scheme - cycle to work scheme for the purchase of a bicycle and accessories for up to £2,000.
Family Friendly leave - enhanced maternity and family friendly leave to all employees such as parental, paternity, compassionate and dependents leave
Eye care - free eye test and £49 towards glasses
Wellbeing Support & benefits - Employee Assistance Programme (EAP), offering 24-hour confidential support and counselling to employees.
Breakfast - fruits, snacks, coffee, tea and bread etc available in the London office daily
Hygiene products - free hygiene products available in the London office
Sabbatical leave - employees with five or more years of continuous service are eligible to request one-month sabbatical leave and ten or more years of continuous service are eligible to request three-month sabbatical leave
Birthday leave - discretionary one-day paid leave on your birthday

subject: Our recommendation: Backend Engineer Python/Data
body:
Hello Divyaprakash,

We recommend this job for you. Take a look and see if you want to apply.



Backend Engineer Python/Data

Richard Wheeler Associates
East London (E1)

Permanent

From £60,000 to £75,000 per annum + benefits

1 day ago





Apply Now
https://click.totaljobsmail.com/f/a/hjbesBuy4YmIgQcCOGDaDA~~/AAAmIgA~_Gk2chuT00UhlyZGl2eWFwcmFrYXNoNzhAZ21haWwuY29tWAQAAAAG


Backend Engineer, Python/Data
Hybrid - 1 day per week in London E1 office. 
£60-75k + strong benefits. 
Our client is a fast-growing health tech scaleup handling data for a million patients (and counting) across the UK and US. Sustained growth has led to this weighty Data-heavy Python Backend opportunity.
We’re seeking a Python Backend Developer (Data-focused) to help take the company's data infrastructure and pipelines to the next level. This exciting role, in a small world-class dev team, will suit a really strong mid-level Python engineer steeped in working in complex backend app environments and now wishing to stretch this into data heavy (data pipelines, Snowflake, ELT, SAS database environ) areas.
The Backend Developer, Data Engineer will have the following responsibilities:
Helping to rebuild core operational and analytical pipelines. You will be core to the design and implementation of both systems. The current tech stack involves Python, PostgreSQL on RDS, Airflow and Snowflake
Helping to rebuild the reporting interfaces across the product and the analytics warehouse. You would be core to creating the infrastructure for this effort as well
Working with the backend team to assist with data optimisation, real-time data queries, and other infrastructure projects
Proactively analysing and improving the quality of the systems: including performance, scalability, maintainability, test coverage and documentation

The following experience is required:
Minimum 3 years of hands-on experience as a Backend Developer, using Python app frameworks
Very comfortable with SQL, preferably PostgreSQL
Growth mindset: a love of learning and resilience in the face of odds
Team mindset: 'we’re in this together, and we support one another in our pursuit'

The following skills/experience are desirable:
CI/CD and modern software testing
Foundational AWS products and systems, such as RDS, S3 and EC2


Read the full job description here
https://click.totaljobsmail.com/f/a/C1jfzm5z8Uz6muh22JB_bA~~/AAAmIgA~~~

Top skills
You're a great fit for this role if you have the following skills:
Python - Postgre-SQL - Realtime - Amazon Web Services - Frameworks -

subject: Save the date: ICC World Test Championship Final 2025 tickets 🎫
body:
Tickets on sale from 31 January

View in browser https://mcc-information.org.uk/cr/AQiCwAMQqZaKBxiY1-xmCrmTgXWse0zun5TMECN38SBB5ik0b_WppuXUBNMrV7c

( https://mcc-information.org.uk/c/AQiCwAMQqZaKBxiY1-xmILvFtaMBKtgFWOY5RSLm0G-STPOFlFpK5s4ZO68nbP1F34kmpV4 )

The ICC World Test Championship Final 2025 will be played at Lord's, with first-time finalists South Africa set to battle it out against defending champions Australia.

From 11-16 June, the Home of Cricket will stage the Final for the first time, during a week-long celebration of the longest format.

The Ultimate Test promises to be another absorbing clash, with the top two sides aiming to lift the iconic ICC World Test Championship mace following two years of intense competition.

Tickets go on sale next week, with a 48-hour ICC priority ticket window live from 10.00 GMT on Wednesday 29 January. To gain access to this priority ticket window, register your interest here ( https://mcc-information.org.uk/c/AQiCwAMQqZaKBxiY1-xmILzFtaMBejjcNj0et0vXLFrvB3ekRkSoGWUljbioFCd05b3vY30 ).

Public tickets will then be made available from 10.00 GMT on Friday 31 January. Keep an eye on your inbox for the on sale link at this time.

Adult tickets start from £45, and U16s from £15. Premium hospitality packages start from £349 + VAT.

( https://mcc-information.org.uk/c/AQiCwAMQqZaKBxiY1-xmILvFtaMBKtgFWOY5RSLm0G-STPOFlFpK5s4ZO68nbP1F34kmpV4 )

car allowance, pension, bonus and benefits

https://click.cwjobs.co.uk/f/a/gthr5cvUWJmpazXgMBeSig~~/AAAmIgA~/RgRpdjtlP4RHAWh0dHBzOi8vd3d3LmN3am9icy5jby51ay9Kb2JTZWFyY2gvRW1haWxMaW5rLmFzcHg_~


We have an exciting opportunity for a Senior Mobile Application Engineer to develop and maintain the mobile app and supporting APIs for Hive Connected Homes. You will work across our full range of products, including Hive Active Heating, Lighting, EV Charging, Sensors & Plugs, and associated subscriptions and services.
Location: Predominantly home-based with occasional travel to Windsor.
Key Responsibilities:
Enhance existing functionality and ensure high performance.

Maintain the app, including dependency upgrades and modernization.

Implement technical improvements and optimizations.

Develop new features and fix bugs within target timeframes.

Participate in code reviews and provide feedback.


Senior Responsibilities:
Lead new projects and exploratory work.

Promote test coverage, code quality, and best practices.

Mentor junior team members.


Technical Capabilities:
Experience with JavaScript/TypeScript, React, and React Native.

Proficiency in unit testing and mobile UI testing frameworks.

Familiarity with Redux/Redux-Saga/Redux Toolkit/RTKQuery.

Experience with iOS/Android development and deployment.

Familiarity with continuous integration tools (CircleCI, Travis, AWS CodeBuild).

Knowledge of AWS Cognito, OAuth, and cloud providers like AWS.


Behavioural Competencies:
Ability to plan, manage, and organize work.

Willingness to learn new technologies.

Strong collaboration skills.

Strategic and tactical thinking.


Perks and Benefits:
Competitive salary and bonus potential.

Company car allowance.

Employee Energy Allowance at 15% of the government price cap.

Pension scheme and healthcare plan.

25 days holiday, plus public holidays, with the option to buy up to 5 additional days.

Flexible benefits, including technology vouchers, an electric car lease scheme, and travel insurance.


Join us at Hive and help shape the future of energy and sustainability. Be a part of something truly innovative and make a real impact on the environment. Apply now and be a part of the Net Zero revolution!

subject: Our recommendation: Software Engineer Python
body:
Hello Divyaprakash,

We recommend this job for you. Take a look and see if you want to apply.



Software Engineer Python

Client Server
The City, City of London (EC2)

Permanent

£60000 - £70000 per annum + benefits

1 day ago





Apply Now
https://click.totaljobsmail.com/f/a/vcfrlDnOE61FiEdRvGsQFg~~/AAAmIgA~_YGejUhlyZGl2eWFwcmFrYXNoNzhAZ21haWwuY29tWAQAAAAG


Software Engineer (Python FAST API AWS) Hybrid WFH to £70k
Are you a bright, ambitious Software Engineer who enjoys working on complex systems with a range of programming languages? You could be progressing your career at a Tech for Good start-up technology company that has recently received £70 million in funding and has secure government backing.
As a Software Engineer you'll design, develop and maintain the core platform, continually seeking improvements and optimisation. You'll focus on backend functionality using Python and FAST APIs within a cloud (AWS) environment but will also have exposure to Next.js and TypeScript on the front end and NumPy, Pandas for data modelling and visualisation. You'll collaborate closely with the CTO and be supported to progress to a senior role within the business.
The company specialise in retrofits for new and existing properties centred around environmental efficiency, enabling construction companies and home owners alike to meet government energy efficiency targets.
Location / WFH:
You can work from home most of the time, meeting up with colleagues in the London or Birmingham office once or twice a week.
About you:
You have achieved a 2.1 or above from a top tier university, Computer Science preferred
You have strong commercial experience within a start-up or SME and have worked across the full development lifecycle
You have strong backend Python development experience
You have experience with FAST APIs (will also consider Flask)
You have a good understanding of AWS, Docker, Terraform, DevOps environments
You're familiar with TypeScript front end tools such as Next.js, it would also be useful to have an appreciation of data modelling and data visualisation
You have excellent communication and collaboration skills

What's in it for you:
Salary to £70k
Hybrid working
Pension
Excellent career growth as the company scales

At Client Server we believe in a diverse workplace that allows people to play to their strengths and continually learn. We're an equal opportunities employer whose people come from all walks of life and will never discriminate based on race, colour, religion, sex, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, national origin, genetics, disability, age, or veteran status. The clients we work with share our values.

Top skills
You're a great fit for this role if you have the following skills:
Python - Flask - NumPy - Amazon Web Services - Terraform -

subject: Our recommendation: Software Engineer Python
body:
Hello Divyaprakash,

We recommend this job for you. Take a look and see if you want to apply.



Software Engineer Python

Client Server
The City, City of London (EC2)

Permanent

£60000 - £70000 per annum + benefits

1 day ago





Apply Now
https://click.cwjobs.co.uk/f/a/_aDZUVuQ3IRcDa1eeU9X8A~~/AAAmIgA~/RgRpdh8iP4RHAWh0dHBzOi8vd3d3LmN3am9icy5jby51ay9Kb2JTZWFyY2gvRW1haWxMaW5rLmFzcHg_~


Software Engineer (Python FAST API AWS) Hybrid WFH to £70k
Are you a bright, ambitious Software Engineer who enjoys working on complex systems with a range of programming languages? You could be progressing your career at a Tech for Good start-up technology company that has recently received £70 million in funding and has secure government backing.
As a Software Engineer you'll design, develop and maintain the core platform, continually seeking improvements and optimisation. You'll focus on backend functionality using Python and FAST APIs within a cloud (AWS) environment but will also have exposure to Next.js and TypeScript on the front end and NumPy, Pandas for data modelling and visualisation. You'll collaborate closely with the CTO and be supported to progress to a senior role within the business.
The company specialise in retrofits for new and existing properties centred around environmental efficiency, enabling construction companies and home owners alike to meet government energy efficiency targets.
Location / WFH:
You can work from home most of the time, meeting up with colleagues in the London or Birmingham office once or twice a week.
About you:
You have achieved a 2.1 or above from a top tier university, Computer Science preferred
You have strong commercial experience within a start-up or SME and have worked across the full development lifecycle
You have strong backend Python development experience
You have experience with FAST APIs (will also consider Flask)
You have a good understanding of AWS, Docker, Terraform, DevOps environments
You're familiar with TypeScript front end tools such as Next.js, it would also be useful to have an appreciation of data modelling and data visualisation
You have excellent communication and collaboration skills

What's in it for you:
Salary to £70k
Hybrid working
Pension
Excellent career growth as the company scales

At Client Server we believe in a diverse workplace that allows people to play to their strengths and continually learn. We're an equal opportunities employer whose people come from all walks of life and will never discriminate based on race, colour, religion, sex, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, national origin, genetics, disability, age, or veteran status. The clients we work with share our values.

Top skills

Python - Flask - NumPy - Amazon Web Services - Terraform -

subject: Struggling with imposter syndrome?
body:
​
Hey Divyaprakash

It’s Michael.

​

I want to share something I don’t talk about often.

​

A few years ago, I saw a job for a Data Analyst.

It was the kind of job I’d been dreaming about.

But instead of feeling excited, I froze.

​

I worried:

* 'Am I even qualified for this?'
* 'What if they look at my application and laugh?'
* 'There’s probably someone with way more experience.'

​

I stared at the job description what felt like forever,
convincing myself I wasn’t good enough.

The longer I sat there, the more reasons I convinced myself I
wouldn’t get the job.

So, I didn’t apply.

​

---------------------------------
A reframe that changed everything
---------------------------------

Months later, I told a friend about the role I didn’t apply for
because I thought I wasn’t ready.

They said something that stuck with me:

“Michael, if you had every skill they wanted, you’d probably get
bored in a few months—and so would they.

Businesses want someone with fresh ideas, room to grow, and the
energy to learn.

If you can make up for any gaps, with extra enthusiasm and your
unique perspective.”

​

They were right.

To avoid the pain of rejection, I’d been talking myself out of
great opportunities.

From that day on, I decided to stop holding myself back.

​

------------------------------
Here’s what I did differently:
------------------------------

* Reframed my experience: Instead of focusing on what I didn’t
have, I looked at how my skills could solve real problems for
employers.
* Built confidence through action: Applying for jobs and reaching
out to people felt intimidating at first, but every step helped
me grow.
* Focused on progress, not perfection: I stopped waiting to feel
“ready” and started taking small steps forward.

​

-----------------------
What this means for you
-----------------------

If you’ve ever hesitated to apply for a role, here’s what I want
you to think about:

* What are 2-3 achievements or skills you’re proud of? How could
these help an employer solve a problem?
* What’s one step you can take today that feels slightly outside
your comfort zone? Maybe it’s reaching out on LinkedIn or
applying for that role you’ve been eyeing.
* How could you reframe your self-talk? Instead of focusing on
what you’re missing, remind yourself of the value you bring.

​

-----------
What’s next
-----------

In the next few emails, I’ll share strategies to help you:

* Build your network with confidence.
* Tell the story of your career so employers see your value.
* Reach out to industry leaders, employers, and recruiters.

​

But here’s the thing: even the best strategy won’t work without
the right mindset.

That’s why I’ll also share the mindset shifts that helped me step
out of my comfort zone and land my dream job.

I want you to experience the same transformation.

​

Talk soon,

Michael

​

P.S.

Are you finding these tips useful?

I'd love to hear from you! Drop by my LinkedIn comment section
here and let me know (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/4zud3lwdwzu7u5zzzl8sxh620lm77i5/7qh7h8hoe275gmbz/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubGlua2VkaW4uY29tL2luL21pY2hhZTFkaTExb24v
).

I share tips every day at 12:45 PM BST and always enjoy chatting
in the comments.

​

​Change your account details (
https://preferences.convertkit-mail2.com/4zud3lwdwzu7u5zzzl8sxh620lm77i5
) | Unsubscribe (
https://unsubscribe.convertkit-mail2.com/4zud3lwdwzu7u5zzzl8sxh620lm77i5
) | Unit 28 Golden Way, Urmston, Manchester, Cheshire M41 0NA

subject: Our recommendation: Senior Developer / Engineer
body:
Hello Divyaprakash,

We recommend this job for you. Take a look and see if you want to apply.



Senior Developer / Engineer

CANADA LIFE
City of London (EC1)

Permanent



1 day ago





Apply Now
https://click.cwjobs.co.uk/f/a/ytiPbNzcb5pUKhNqcoLozg~~/AAAmIgA~/RgRpdgMwP4RHAWh0dHBzOi8vd3d3LmN3am9icy5jby51ay9Kb2JTZWFyY2gvRW1haWxMaW5rLmFzcHg_~


Location: London, Potters Bar, Bristol or Isle of Man (Hybrid working options available)

At Canada Life UK, we’re dedicated to supporting the retirement, investment, and protection needs of individuals, families, and companies. Part of Great-West Lifeco, we’ve been a trusted presence in the UK since 1903. Our mission is to build better futures for our customers, intermediaries, and employees by fostering a modern, agile, and inclusive environment.

We’re on a journey to transform our business, focusing on financial and tax planning expertise, home finance and annuities solutions, and collective fund offerings. Our ambition is clear: to create a customer-focused, digitally driven future.


About the Role

Are you ready to lead the charge in digital innovation? As a Senior Engineer, you’ll play a pivotal role in shaping the future of our digital solutions. This is an opportunity to drive meaningful outcomes and make a real impact.

Canada Life UK is modernising its IT estate, leveraging cloud technologies and automation while adopting a product-centric approach. You'll be involved at every stage of the product lifecycle, from conception and design to implementation and operational support.

While this is a full-stack role, we are particularly keen to augment our team with individuals who have strong skills in UI/UX and a genuine focus on customer-centric solutions. We’re looking for candidates who bring diverse experiences, innovative thinking, and a collaborative mindset to create intuitive and engaging user interfaces that delight our customers.
What You’ll Do
 
Design, build, deploy, and support software across front-end and back-end stacks, with a particular emphasis on delivering exceptional user experiences.
Configure and maintain automated CI/CD pipelines for seamless Azure-hosted solutions.
Adopt a product mindset, focusing on customer outcomes and data-driven decisions.



Key Responsibilities

1. Solution Development
 
Contribute hands-on to the full development lifecycle, from coding to production release.
Collaborate closely with team members, product owners, and stakeholders, ensuring customer needs are at the forefront.


2. Continuous Learning
 
Stay ahead of industry trends and continually enhance your skills to drive innovation.
Share knowledge to strengthen our technical community.


3. DevOps Delivery
 
Implement and refine DevOps practices to balance development and operations.
Drive automation and reliability while reducing technical debt.



About You
 
Expertise in modern component-oriented front-end frameworks and libraries with a strong appreciation for user experience (UX) and customer-focused design.
Familiarity in a Microsoft/Azure tech stack
Experience with CI/CD pipelines and tools (e.g., Azure DevOps, Octopus Deploy) or a strong understanding of continuous deployment principles.
Passionate about agile practices and small iterations to optimise feedback loops.
Awareness of security best practices to ensure robust software delivery.
A collaborative mindset, contributing to team and community excellence.
Open to applying innovative ideas and approaches, regardless of your previous industry background.
 

How we work at Canada Life
Our culture is unique and incredibly important to us. We care about doing the right thing for our people, customers and community and helping others to build better futures. Our blueprint behaviours shape and influence how we work, and are central to the relationships we have with others. Every day we are encouraged to be more curious, own the outcome, face into things together and find a way forward.
We want colleagues to have rewarding careers with us so we invest in the development of our people, technology and workplaces. That’s why we offer a range of training, flexible working and opportunities to grow and develop.
Diversity and inclusion
Building an inclusive workplace with a diverse workforce where everyone can feel they belong and achieve their potential regardless of gender, ethnicity or any other characteristic is a key commitment for us. We are proud of the progress we’re making in DEI, and we continue for it to be a significant focus.
“At Canada Life we believe in the power of great people from different backgrounds, experiences and perspectives coming together to build better futures. Emerging talent is crucial to our growth and creating an environment that continues to inspire us all.” Nick Harding, Chief People Officer, Canada Life UK
We appreciate that everyone has different work and life responsibilities. We’re happy to discuss flexible working arrangements, including part time, for any of our roles should this be a requirement for you.
 
We are committed to building an inclusive workplace where everyone feels they belong and can achieve their potential. Our progress in Diversity, Equity, and Inclusion (DEI) reflects our belief in the power of diverse perspectives to build better futures.
Flexible Working
We understand that everyone’s circumstances are unique. We’re happy to discuss flexible or part-time working arrangements to support your needs.
Join Us
If you’re ready to make an impact in a supportive, forward-thinking environment, we’d love to hear from you. Bring your unique perspective, creativity, and passion for delivering great digital experiences. Apply today and help us shape the future of digital innovation at Canada Life UK.

subject: Our recommendation: Senior Research Scientist
body:
Hello Divyaprakash,

We recommend this job for you. Take a look and see if you want to apply.



Senior Research Scientist

Huawei
London

Permanent

Competitive

1 day ago





Apply Now
https://click.totaljobsmail.com/f/a/nLBe9YZxgONymeajRAuEGA~~/AAAmIgA~-xxk2f-KGvmUhlyZGl2eWFwcmFrYXNoNzhAZ21haWwuY29tWAQAAAAG


About Huawei Research and Development UK Limited
Founded in 1987, Huawei is a leading global provider of information and communications technology (ICT) infrastructure and smart devices. We have 207,000 employees and operate in over 170 countries and regions, serving more than three billion people around the world.
Our vision and mission is to bring digital to every person, home and organization for a fully connected, intelligent world. To this end, we will drive ubiquitous connectivity and promote equal access to networks; bring cloud and artificial intelligence to all four corners of the earth to provide superior computing power where you need it, when you need it; build digital platforms to help all industries and organizations become more agile, efficient, and dynamic; redefine user experience with AI, making it more personalized for people in all aspects of their life, whether they’re at home, in the office, or on the go.
This spirit of innovation has led Huawei to work in close partnership with leading academic institutions in the UK to develop and refine the latest technologies. With a shared commitment to innovation and progress, both parties have worked together to achieve common goals and establish a strong partnership. The partnership between UK and Huawei help to develop the technologies of the future that will transform the way we all communicate, work and live.
For the past 30 years we have maintained an unwavering focus, rejecting shortcuts and easy opportunities that don't align with our core business. With a practical approach to everything we do, we concentrate our efforts and invest patiently to drive technological breakthroughs.
This strategic focus is a reflection of our core values:
staying customer-centric
inspiring dedication
persevering
growing by reflection

Huawei Research and Development UK Limited Overview
Huawei’s vision is a fully connected, intelligent world. To achieve this, we work to inspire passion for basic research around the world. Our combined passion drives development across the global innovation value chain. Huawei has the largest Research and Development organization in the world with 96,000+ employees in research centers around the globe. In the UK, we already have design centers in Cambridge, London, Edinburgh and Ipswich. We continue to explore and define new research directions and new services. We have expanded our collaborations with academic researchers; researched new network architectures, integration of communications and key enabling technologies; and developed the fundamental theories of these technologies. We invite you to join us on this exciting journey and drive your career forward.
Job Summary
The AI Theory group at the London Research Center is seeking a Research Scientist to contribute to the development of the theoretical and algorithmic foundation for AIGC. The team is tackling ambitious projects focusing on AIGC theory and Multimodal text-and-image/video generation. The ideal candidate should have experience in LLM and Multimodal-LLM, Generative Modelling (Diffusion Models, Auto-regressive Models, Transformers), and/or Efficient Learning (Data Efficiency, Optimization Theory)
The research scientist will conduct both academic and applied research. They will aim to advance the state-of-the-art in multimodal modelling with top tier conference publications and will collaboratively develop advanced products and services with other groups in the company.
Key Responsibilities:
Leading and participating in cutting-edge research projects, focusing on the theoretical and algorithmic foundation of AIGC.
Devising, prototyping and patenting innovative solutions in collaboration with product teams.
External engagement: drafting academic publications, giving talks and collaborating with academic leaders.
Mentoring research interns and junior researchers.

This job description is only an outline of the tasks, responsibilities and outcomes required of the role. The jobholder will carry out any other duties as may be reasonably required by his/her line manager. The job description and personal specification may be reviewed on an ongoing basis in accordance with the changing needs of Huawei Research and Development UK Limited.
Person Specification:
Required:

PhD degree computer science or related field; or equivalent research experience.

Hands on experience with image/video generation and/or (multimodal) large language models.

Strong research track record. E.g. have published in top tier conferences including NeurIPS, ICLR, ICML, CVPR, ICCV; and journals including JMLR and TPAMI, etc.

Strong coding skills: ability to quickly prototype in Python.
Excellent written and oral communication skills.

Desired:

Passionate about (multimodal) large language models, text-to-image/video model, controllable generation.

Experience mentoring other junior researchers.

Experience working in industry and collaborating with product groups.

Experience with PyTorch Profiler, Accelerate/DeepSpeed/Megatron/ HuggingFace PEFT.
Hands on experience with ViTs, (Multimodal)-LLMs, Diffusions, (Video) VAEs, etc.

What we offer
33 days annual leave entitlement per year (including UK public holidays)
Group Personal Pension
Life insurance
Private medical insurance
Medical expense claim scheme
Employee Assistance Program
Cycle to work scheme
Company sports club and social events
Additional time off for learning and development

subject: Our recommendation: Scala Developer
body:
Hello Divyaprakash,

We recommend this job for you. Take a look and see if you want to apply.



Scala Developer

TEKsystems
Birmingham, West Midlands

Contract

400.00 - 550.00 GBP/Daily

2 days ago





Apply Now
https://click.cwjobs.co.uk/f/a/ijqy0kFdTR6vcb1bNA5VoQ~~/AAAmIgA~/RgRpdecuP4RHAWh0dHBzOi8vd3d3LmN3am9icy5jby51ay9Kb2JTZWFyY2gvRW1haWxMaW5rLmFzcHg_~


Job Title: Scala Developer Job Description
We are seeking a talented Scala Play Front End Web Developer to join an existing team for a well known IT Services customer of ours. In this role, you will be responsible for developing and maintaining high-quality web applications using Scala and Play framework.
Responsibilities
Develop and maintain front end web applications using Scala and Play framework.
Collaborate with cross-functional teams to define, design, and ship new features.
Ensure the performance, quality, and responsiveness of applications.
Identify and correct bottlenecks and fix bugs.
Help maintain code quality, organisation, and automation.

Essential Skills Proficiency in Scala programming language.
Experience with Play framework.
Strong understanding of front end development.
Ability to write clean, readable, and maintainable code.

Why Work Here? Join a dynamic team where your contributions are valued and your growth is supported. Enjoy a collaborative work environment with opportunities for professional development and career advancement.
Job Type & Location
This is a Contract position initially 6 Months with a potential to renew until 2027.
Location
Birmingham, UK
Rate/Salary
400.00 - 550.00 GBP Daily

subject: Our recommendation: Senior DevOps Engineer
body:
Hello Divyaprakash,

We recommend this job for you. Take a look and see if you want to apply.



Senior DevOps Engineer

Ansys
East Midlands

Permanent

Competitive

1 day ago





Apply Now
https://click.totaljobsmail.com/f/a/QtSVnKFUyiKVTfDJ2WED_A~~/AAAmIgA~


Requisition #: 16014
Our Mission: Powering Innovation That Drives Human Advancement
When visionary companies need to know how their world-changing ideas will perform, they close the gap between design and reality with Ansys simulation. For more than 50 years, Ansys software has enabled innovators across industries to push boundaries by using the predictive power of simulation. From sustainable transportation to advanced semiconductors, from satellite systems to life-saving medical devices, the next great leaps in human advancement will be powered by Ansys.
Innovate With Ansys, Power Your Career.
The Senior Site Reliability Engineer at Ansys is responsible for the reliability and availability of systems and services and the infrastructure activities of multiple software products and supporting systems. While automation is a part of SRE, this role is more directed towards ensuring the reliability of systems. SRE's at Ansys use automation to minimize manual intervention and enhance system stability. In this role, the Senior SRE will use advanced technical and problem-solving skills to help the team tackle complex issues, satisfy customer requirements, and accomplish development objectives.
Key Duties and Responsibilities
Collaborates with others to brainstorm best techniques to resolve complex technological infrastructure, build or packaging problems

As a member of the SRE team, you will work with development teams to help create automated pipelines and solutions required for continuous delivery

Have a consultant's mindset - you LISTEN, and lead your customers into the goodness of SRE practices

Recognize your obligation to the team to elevate the practice of SRE to the highest standard possible

Improve predictability and reliability of software releases, workflows, and operating software

Reduce complexity and streamline delivery by participating in the creation of and promoting the use of reusable code, tooling, systems, and solution patterns

Be anexpert in incident responses... I.e., can quickly identify and resolve incidents to maintain high system reliability
Measure and monitor metrics and alarms extensively to ensure the performance and reliability of systems. Decisions should be driven by a data-driven approach.

Minimum Education/Certification Requirements and Experience
BS in Engineering, Computer Science, or related field of study with 5+ years’ experience, MS with 3 years experience, or PhD with 1 year experience

At least 3 years of experience with source code version control software (git) and AWS Cloud

At least 3 years of working with Terraform with a deep understanding of module creation and best practices

Proficient in at least one language used for scripting (e.g. bash, python, perl, ruby, etc)


Preferred Qualifications and Skills
Thorough knowledge of software development tools, compilers, and packaging software

Extensive knowledge of Linux operating systems

Passion for crafting robust and efficient automated build systems

Good communication and interpersonal skills


#li-remote
At Ansys, we know that changing the world takes vision, skill, and each other. We fuel new ideas, build relationships, and help each other realize our greatest potential. We are ONE Ansys. We operate on three key components: the commitments to our stakeholders, the behaviors of how we work together, and the actions of how we deliver results. Together as ONE Ansys, we are powering innovation that drives human advancement.
Our Commitments:
Amaze with innovative products and solutions
Make our customers incredibly successful
Act with integrity
Ensure employees thrive and shareholders prosper

Our Values:
Adaptability: Be open, welcome what's next
Courage: Be courageous, move forward passionately
Generosity: Be generous, share, listen, serve
Authenticity: Be you, make us stronger

Our Actions:
We commit to audacious goals
We work seamlessly as a team
We demonstrate mastery
We deliver outstanding results

INCLUSION IS AT OUR CORE 
We believe diverse thinking leads to better outcomes. We are committed to creating and nurturing a workplace that fuels this by welcoming people, no matter their background, identity, or experience, to a workplace where they are valued and where diversity, inclusion, equity, and belonging thrive.

WELCOME WHAT’S NEXT IN YOUR CAREER AT ANSYS
At Ansys, you will find yourself among the sharpest minds and most visionary leaders across the globe. Collectively we strive to change the world with innovative technology and transformational solutions. With a prestigious reputation in working with well-known, world-class companies, standards at Ansys are high — met by those willing to rise to the occasion and meet those challenges head on. Our team is passionate about pushing the limits of world-class simulation technology, empowering our customers to turn their design concepts into successful, innovative products faster and at a lower cost.
At Ansys, it’s about the learning, the discovery, and the collaboration. It’s about the “what’s next” as much as the “mission accomplished.” And it’s about the melding of disciplined intellect with strategic direction and results that have, can, and do impact real people in real ways. All this is forged within a working environment built on respect, autonomy, and ethics.

CREATING A PLACE WE’RE PROUD TO BE 
Ansys is an S&P 500 company and a member of the NASDAQ-100. We are proud to have been recognized for the following more recent awards, although our list goes on: Newsweek’s Most Loved Workplace globally and in the U.S., Gold Stevie Award Winner, America’s Most Responsible Companies, Fast Company World Changing Ideas, Great Place to Work Certified (Belgium, China, Greece, France, India, Japan, Korea, Spain, Sweden, Taiwan, and U.K.).

For more information, please visit us at www.ansys.com

Ansys is an Equal Opportunity Employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, disability, veteran status, and other protected characteristics.

Ansys does not accept unsolicited referrals for vacancies, and any unsolicited referral will become the property of Ansys. Upon hire, no fee will be owed to the agency, person, or entity.

Accelerate your public policy career with the 1-year online master's degree


Applications for the M.A. in Public Policy degree from the O.P. Jindal Global University are now open!

 

Why should you consider applying?

  • Duration: Now streamlined to 1 year, enabling you to achieve your career goals faster.
  • Curriculum: An interdisciplinary curriculum designed to address political, economic, social, and environmental challenges, with a special focus on developing economies.
  • Specialisations: Data Analytics Track for those aiming to leverage data-driven insights in policy-making roles within government, non-profits, or consulting, Policy Design Track ideal for careers in government, international organizations, NGOs, and consulting, preparing graduates for roles like policy analysts and program evaluators.
  • Flexible learning: A completely virtual experience with weekly modules accessible through video playback or interactive transcripts, allowing you to learn at your own pace.
  • Expert instruction:Learn from both academic experts and policy practitioners from esteemed organizations such as the UN, Commonwealth Secretariat, ILO, and World Bank.
  • Diverse peer group: Join a heterogeneous peer group to build competencies in problem-solving, leadership, communication, accountability, and social sensitivity.
 

Eligibility:
Open to candidates from diverse backgrounds with an undergraduate degree in any field from a recognized university in India or abroad.

Start your application today.

Have questions? Please get in touch by emailing us at online@jgu.edu.in

 
Apply now

subject: Build a foundation for gen AI success with AWS
body:
Innovate faster with the most comprehensive set of AI capabilities

As a technology leader, driving successful gen AI adoption is critical, but scaling beyond pilot projects presents obstacles. For long-term success, organizations need access to a comprehensive set of tools and infrastructure to meet evolving needs, now and in the future. Learn how businesses are building a strong gen AI foundation on AWS to drive tangible value quickly and securely.

Build a foundation for success in the gen AI era

From transforming how work gets done with gen AI apps to quickly creating innovative gen AI apps with robust models and tools to cost-effectively building and training FMs at scale, explore this infographic to learn how businesses are building the right foundation to succeed with gen AI on AWS.

Explore the infographic › <https://email.awscloud.com/MTEyLVRaTS03NjYAAAGYNYOS-JubqQsPZpiuI-hNIoJLOmwrZQDZ1IsuO0ht9SGNF7o17zH42YYK8K_cCcQUbQIiw8g=>

6 key guidelines for building secure and reliable gen AI applications on Amazon Bedrock

Quickly create innovative gen AI apps with Amazon Bedrock. This whitepaper reveals 6 key guidelines to build secure, reliable, and high-performing AI apps. Learn how Ferrari and DoorDash are leveraging the broad access to top FMs provided by Amazon Bedrock to simplify app development and fuel innovation.

Read the whitepaper › <https://email.awscloud.com/MTEyLVRaTS03NjYAAAGYNYOS-Zonqx4Pi4p0fbHDlZONnDrP71qgGYwx1s7zxBVbX1-A9_SJBMTpLvRZOamnSBPByG4=>












Generative AI on AWS

Boost productivity, build differentiated experiences, and innovate faster with AWS.


Get started › <https://email.awscloud.com/MTEyLVRaTS03NjYAAAGYNYOS-P4FMdxdviQMrSYiKiyJop9TNyxamj7vNY3VoF5Y-kIbnaWbYsv0aR4Xm-lXzeD58jc=>

===

Data and AI Services

With AWS, you can build a data foundation to power all your gen AI use cases.
